table_lines.comment: The upper limit of the energy window, in KeV.

table_lines.name: Secondary Counts Type
table_lines.comment: Array defining the type of additional counts accumulated during acquisition.

table_lines.name: Scan Progression Direction
table_lines.comment: The anatomical order in which the slices were acquired.

table_lines.name: Radiopharmaceutical Information Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that describe isotope information.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the radionuclide.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Route
table_lines.comment: Route of administration.

table_lines.name: >Administration Route Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the administration route of the radiopharmaceutical.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Volume
table_lines.comment: Volume of administered radiopharmaceutical in cubic cm.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Start Time
table_lines.comment:
Time of start of administration. The actual time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes, using the same time base as Series Time (0008,0031).
The use of this Attribute is deprecated in favor of Radiopharmaceutical Start DateTime (0018,1078).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Start DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time of start of administration. The actual date and time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes, using the same time base as Series Time (0008,0031).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Stop Time
table_lines.comment:
Time of end of administration. The actual ending time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes, using the same time base as Series Time (0008,0031).
The use of this Attribute is deprecated in favor of Radiopharmaceutical Stop DateTime (0018,1079).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Stop DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time of end of administration. The actual ending date and time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes, using the same time base as Series Time (0008,0031).

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Total Dose
table_lines.comment: The radiopharmaceutical dose administered to the patient measured in Becquerels (Bq) at the Radiopharmaceutical Start Time (0018,1072).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Administration Event UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identification of the administration of the radiopharmaceutical to the patient.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Half Life
table_lines.comment: The radionuclide half life, in seconds, that was used in the correction of this image.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Positron Fraction
table_lines.comment: The radionuclide positron fraction (fraction of decays that are by positron emission) that was used in the correction of this image.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Specific Activity
table_lines.comment: The activity per unit mass of the radiopharmaceutical, in Bq/micromole, at the Radiopharmaceutical Start Time (0018,1072).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical
table_lines.comment: Name of the radiopharmaceutical.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the radiopharmaceutical.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Intervention Drug Information Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that describes the intervention drugs used.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Intervention Drug Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the intervention drug.

table_lines.name: >Intervention Drug Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the intervention drug name.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Intervention Drug Start Time
table_lines.comment: Time of administration of the intervention drug, using the same time base as for Series Time (0008,0031).

table_lines.name: >Intervention Drug Stop Time
table_lines.comment: Time of completion of administration of the intervention drug, using the same time base as for Series Time (0008,0031).

table_lines.name: >Intervention Drug Dose
table_lines.comment: Intervention drug dose, in mg.

table_lines.name: Beat Rejection Flag
table_lines.comment: Heart beat duration sorting has been applied.

table_lines.name: Trigger Source or Type
table_lines.comment: Text indicating trigger source.

table_lines.name: PVC Rejection
table_lines.comment: Description of the type of PVC rejection criteria used.

table_lines.name: Skip Beats
table_lines.comment: Number of beats skipped after a detected arrhythmia.

table_lines.name: Heart Rate
table_lines.comment: Average number of heart beats per minute for the collection period for this image. This shall include all accepted beats as well as rejected beats.

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples (planes) in this image.

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits allocated.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits stored. The value shall be the same as the value in Bits Allocated (0028,0100).

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit. Shall be one less than the value in Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Rescale Intercept
table_lines.comment: The value b in relationship between stored values (SV) and pixel value units (U) defined in Units (0054,1001): U = m*SV+b. The Rescale Intercept is always zero for PET images.

table_lines.name: Rescale Slope
table_lines.comment: m in the equation specified in Rescale Intercept (0028,1052).

table_lines.name: Trigger Time
table_lines.comment: Time interval, in msec, from the start of the trigger to the beginning of data acquisition for this image. Required if Series Type (0054,1000), Value 1 is GATED.

table_lines.name: Low R-R Value
table_lines.comment: R-R interval lower limit for beat rejection, in msec. Required if Series Type (0054,1000), Value 1 is GATED and Beat Rejection Flag (0018,1080) is Y.

table_lines.name: High R-R Value
table_lines.comment: R-R interval upper limit for beat rejection, in msec. Required if Series Type (0054,1000), Value 1 is GATED and Beat Rejection Flag (0018,1080) is Y.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See
Required if Lossy Compression has been performed on the image. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Nominal Interval
table_lines.comment: Average duration of accepted beats, in msec, of the R-R interval.

table_lines.name: Intervals Acquired
table_lines.comment: Number of heartbeats that fall within Low R-R Value (0018,1081) and High R-R Value (0018,1082), and were therefore accepted and contribute coincidence events to this R-R Interval.

table_lines.name: Intervals Rejected
table_lines.comment: Number of heartbeats that fall outside Low R-R Value (0018,1081) and High R-R Value (0018,1082), and do not contribute coincidence events to this R-R Interval. However, they may contribute coincidence events to other R-R Intervals.

table_lines.name: Primary (Prompts) Counts Accumulated
table_lines.comment: The sum of events that occur in the primary event channel. The counts include Trues +Scatter+ Randoms if Randoms Correction Method (0054,1100) is NONE; otherwise the counts are Trues +Scatter.

table_lines.name: Slice Sensitivity Factor
table_lines.comment: The slice-to-slice sensitivity correction factor that was used to correct this image. The value shall be one if no slice sensitivity correction was applied.

table_lines.name: Decay Factor
table_lines.comment: The decay factor that was used to scale this image. Required if Decay Correction (0054,1102) is other than NONE. If decay correction is applied, all images in the Series shall be decay corrected to the same time.

table_lines.name: Scatter Fraction Factor
table_lines.comment: An estimate of the fraction of acquired counts that were due to scatter and were corrected in this image. The value shall be zero if no scatter correction was applied.

table_lines.name: Dead Time Factor
table_lines.comment: The average dead time correction factor that was applied to this image. The value shall be one if no dead time correction was applied.

table_lines.usage: No CID for the Anatomic Region Sequence is defined.

table_lines.name: Isocenter Position
table_lines.comment: Isocenter coordinates (x,y,z), in mm. Specifies the location of the machine isocenter in the Patient-Based Coordinate System associated with the Frame of Reference. It allows transformation from the Equipment-Based Coordinate System to the Patient-Based Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the images in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Presentation Intent Type
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the intent of the images that are contained within this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Image Laterality
table_lines.comment:
Laterality of (possibly paired) body part (as described in Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218)) examined.
Shall be consistent with any laterality information contained in Primary Anatomic Structure Modifier Sequence (0008,2230), if present.

table_lines.name: Image Type
table_lines.comment:
Image identification characteristics.
See

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples in this image.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment: Specifies the intended interpretation of the pixel data.

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment:
Most significant bit for pixel sample data.
Shall be one less than the value in Bit Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Pixel Representation
table_lines.comment: Data representation of the pixel samples.

table_lines.name: Pixel Intensity Relationship
table_lines.comment:
The relationship between the Pixel sample values and the X-Ray beam intensity.
See

table_lines.name: Pixel Intensity Relationship Sign
table_lines.comment:
The sign of the relationship between the Pixel sample values stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) and the X-Ray beam intensity.
See

m in the equation specified by Rescale Intercept (0028,1052).

table_lines.name: Detector Active Time
table_lines.comment: Time in mSec that the detector is active during acquisition of this image.

RECTANGLE: row dimension followed by column.
ROUND: diameter.
HEXAGONAL: diameter of a circumscribed circle.

table_lines.name: Field of View Origin
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the TLHC of a rectangle circumscribing the Field of View, that is the image pixels stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), before rotation or flipping, from the TLHC of the physical detector area measured in physical detector pixels as a row offset followed by a column offset.
Required if Field of View Rotation (0018,7032) or Field of View Horizontal Flip (0018,7034) is present.
See

table_lines.name: Field of View Rotation
table_lines.comment:
Clockwise rotation in degrees of Field of View, that is the image pixels stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), relative to the physical detector.
Required if Field of View Horizontal Flip (0018,7034) is present.
See

table_lines.name: Field of View Horizontal Flip
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not a horizontal flip has been applied to the Field of View, that is the image pixels stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), after rotation relative to the physical detector as described in Field of View Rotation (0018,7032).
Required if Field of View Rotation (0018,7032) is present.
See

table_lines.name: Imager Pixel Spacing
table_lines.comment: The value of this Attribute shall never be adjusted to account for correction for the effect of geometric magnification or calibration against an object of known size; Pixel Spacing (0028,0030) is specified for that purpose.

table_lines.name: Plate ID

table_lines.name: Detector Type

table_lines.name: Detector Mode

table_lines.name: Detector ID
table_lines.comment: The ID or serial number of the detector used to acquire this image.

table_lines.name: Date of Last Detector Calibration
table_lines.comment: The date on which the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) was last calibrated.

table_lines.name: Time of Last Detector Calibration
table_lines.comment: The time at which the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) was last calibrated.

table_lines.name: Exposures on Detector Since Last Calibration
table_lines.comment: Total number of X-Ray exposures that have been made on the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) since it was calibrated.

table_lines.name: Exposures on Detector Since Manufactured
table_lines.comment: Total number of X-Ray exposures that have been made on the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) since it was manufactured.

table_lines.name: Detector Time Since Last Exposure
table_lines.comment: Time in Seconds since an exposure was last made on this detector prior to the acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: Detector Binning
table_lines.comment: Number of active detectors used to generate a single pixel. Specified as number of row detectors per pixel then column.

table_lines.name: Detector Manufacturer Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the manufacturer of the detector component of the acquisition system

table_lines.name: Detector Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment: Model name of the detector component of the acquisition system

table_lines.name: Detector Conditions Nominal Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the detector is operating within normal tolerances during this image acquisition.

table_lines.name: Detector Temperature
table_lines.comment: Detector temperature during exposure in degrees Celsius.

table_lines.name: Sensitivity
table_lines.comment: Detector sensitivity in manufacturer specific units.

table_lines.name: Detector Element Physical Size
table_lines.comment:

Expressed as row dimension followed by column.

table_lines.name: Detector Active Shape
table_lines.comment: Shape of the active area.

table_lines.name: Detector Active Dimension(s)
table_lines.comment:
Dimensions in mm of the active area.
If Detector Active Shape (0018,7024) is:
RECTANGLE: row dimension followed by column.
ROUND: diameter.
HEXAGONAL: diameter of a circumscribed circle.

table_lines.name: Detector Active Origin
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the TLHC of a rectangle circumscribing the active detector area from the TLHC of a rectangle circumscribing the physical detector area, measured in physical detector pixels as a row offset followed by a column offset.

table_lines.name: View Position

Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

Distance in mm from source to detector center.
See

table_lines.comment: Ratio of Source Image Receptor Distance (SID) over Source Object Distance (SOD).

table_lines.name: Positioner Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray beam about the patient from the RAO to LAO direction where movement from RAO to vertical is positive, if Positioner Type (0018,1508) is CARM.
See
See

table_lines.name: Positioner Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray beam about the patient from the CAU to CRA direction where movement from CAU to vertical is positive, if Positioner Type (0018,1508) is CARM.
See
See

table_lines.name: Detector Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in the row direction in degrees relative to the normal to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward higher numbered columns. Negative values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward lower numbered columns.
See
See

table_lines.name: Detector Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in the column direction in degrees relative to the normal to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward lower numbered rows. Negative values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward higher numbered rows.
See
See

table_lines.name: Column Angulation
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in degree relative to an orthogonal axis to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the tilt is toward the head of the table.
Only meaningful if Positioner Type (0018,1508) is COLUMN.

table_lines.name: Table Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of table plane in degrees relative to horizontal plane [Gravity plane]. Positive values indicate that the head of the table is upward.
Only meaningful if Table Type (0018,113A) is TILTING.

table_lines.comment: The average compression pressure applied to the body part during exposure, calculated in kPa.

table_lines.name: Compression Contact Area
table_lines.comment: The area of the body part to which compression has been applied during exposure, measured in mm2.

table_lines.name: Paddle Description

table_lines.comment: Coordinates of localizing cursor position with respect to pixels in the image specified by a column (delimiter) row pair. The values shall be in the range 0\0 (TLHC) to Columns\Rows (BRHC).

table_lines.comment:
The calculated target position (x, y, z) in mm in an equipment relative right-handed coordinate system where the origin is under the central X-Ray beam at the chest wall, and a z value of zero is located at the surface that the breast is in contact with that is closest to the detector.
X is parallel to the chest wall, y is positive toward the patient's nipple, and z is positive toward the X-Ray source.

table_lines.name: >Displayed Z Value
table_lines.comment: The z value in mm displayed to the user at the time of biopsy.

table_lines.name: >Target Label

table_lines.comment:
Number of acquisition focal planes used for extended depth of field.
Required if Extended Depth of Field (0048,0012) value is YES

table_lines.name: Distance Between Focal Planes
table_lines.comment:
Distance between acquisition focal planes used for extended depth of field, in um.
Required if Extended Depth of Field (0048,0012) value is YES.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Device Processing Description
table_lines.comment: Description of visual processing performed on the image prior to exchange. Examples of this processing are: edge enhanced, gamma corrected, convolved (spatially filtered)

table_lines.name: Convolution Kernel
table_lines.comment: Label for convolution kernel used in acquisition device visual processing

table_lines.name: Number of Optical Paths
table_lines.comment:
Number of Items in the Optical Path Sequence (0048,0105).
Required if Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Optical Path Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the optical paths used during the acquisition of this image.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Optical Path Identifier
table_lines.comment: Identifier for the optical path specified in the Sequence Item. The identifier shall be unique for each Item within the Optical Path Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Optical Path Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the optical path specified in the Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: >Illuminator Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Type of illuminator.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Illumination Wave Length
table_lines.comment: Nominal wavelength of the illuminator in nm. Required if Illumination Color Code Sequence (0048,ee08) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Illumination Color Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Color of the illuminator.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Illumination Wave Length (0022,0055) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Illumination Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Light Path Filter Type Stack Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Filters used in the light source (excitation) path.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Light Path Filter Pass-Through Wavelength
table_lines.comment: Nominal pass-through wavelength of light path filter(s) in nm

table_lines.name: >Light Path Filter Pass Band
table_lines.comment:
Pass band of light path filter(s) in nm. This Attribute has two Values. The first is the shorter and the second the longer wavelength relative to the peak. The values are for the - 3dB nominal (1/2 of peak) pass through intensity.
One of the two Values may be zero length, in which case it is a cutoff filter.

table_lines.name: >Image Path Filter Type Stack Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes stack of filters used in image (emission) path between the imaging target and the optical sensor.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Image Path Filter Pass-Through Wavelength
table_lines.comment: Nominal pass-through wavelength of image path filter(s) in nm

table_lines.name: >Image Path Filter Pass Band
table_lines.comment:
Pass band of image path filter(s) in nm. This Attribute has two Values. The first is the shorter and the second the longer wavelength relative to the peak. The values are for the - 3dB nominal (1/2 of peak) pass through intensity.
One of the two Values may be zero length, in which case it is a cutoff filter

table_lines.name: >Lenses Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Lenses that were used in this optical path.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Condenser Lens Power
table_lines.comment: Nominal power of the condenser lens

table_lines.name: >Objective Lens Power
table_lines.comment: Nominal power of the objective lens. If a single lens is used as both condenser and objective, its power is specified in this Attribute.

table_lines.name: >Objective Lens Numerical Aperture
table_lines.comment: Nominal numerical aperture of the objective lens.

table_lines.name: >Channel Description Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the light color sensed for each channel to generate the image.
Required if this differs from the natural interpretation.
Shall have the same number of Items as the value of Samples per Pixel Used (0028,0003) if present, or otherwise the value of Samples per Pixel (0028,0002). The channels shall be described in the order in which the channels are encoded.

table_lines.usage: CID may be defined in the IOD constraints.

table_lines.name: >Palette Color Lookup Table Sequence
table_lines.comment:
For MONOCHROME2 images, provides a transform of the pixel values with this optical path into an RGB color representation. The LUT provides a mapping to an appropriate color or pseudo-color for display purposes.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >ICC Profile
table_lines.comment: Required if Photometric Interpretation (0028,0004) is not MONOCHROME2, or if Palette Color Lookup Table Sequence (0048,0120) is present.

table_lines.name: >Color Space
table_lines.comment:
A label that identifies the well-known color space of the image. Shall be consistent with any ICC Profile (0028,2000) that is also present.
See

table_lines.name: Plane Position (Slide) Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes position of frame in the Total Pixel Matrix and in the Slide Coordinate System Frame of Reference.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Column Position In Total Image Pixel Matrix
>Row Position In Total Image Pixel Matrix
>X Offset in Slide Coordinate System
table_lines.comment: figure_C.8-16

table_lines.name: >Y Offset in Slide Coordinate System
table_lines.comment: figure_C.8-16

table_lines.name: >Z Offset in Slide Coordinate System
table_lines.comment: figure_C.8-17

table_lines.name: Optical Path Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the optical path characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Specimen Reference Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies specimens that may be visible in this frame, and are fully identified in the Specimen Description Sequence (0040,0560).
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Barcode Value
table_lines.comment: Barcode interpreted from the scanned slide label.

table_lines.name: Label Text
table_lines.comment: Label text interpreted from the scanned slide label, e.g., by optical character recognition.

C.8.12.9-1.table_caption: Whole Slide Microscopy Image Frame Type Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Whole Slide Microscopy Image Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the characteristics of this Whole Slide Microscopy Image frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008). See

table_lines.name: Camera Owner Name
table_lines.comment: The owner of the photographic equipment.

table_lines.name: Lens Specification
table_lines.comment: The minimum focal length, maximum focal length, minimum F number in the minimum focal length, and minimum F number in the maximum focal length for the lens that was used.

table_lines.name: Lens Make
table_lines.comment: The lens manufacturer.

table_lines.name: Lens Model
table_lines.comment: The lens's model name and model number.

table_lines.name: Lens Serial Number
table_lines.comment: The serial number of the lens that was used.

table_lines.name: White Point
table_lines.comment: The chromaticity of the white point of the image. This is the chromaticity when each of the primaries has its reference white value. The value is described using the 1931 CIE xy chromaticity diagram.

table_lines.name: Primary Chromaticities
table_lines.comment: The chromaticity of the three primary colors of the image. This is the chromaticity for each of the primaries when it has its reference white value and the other primaries have their reference black values. These values are described using the 1931 CIE xy chromaticity diagram.

table_lines.name: Battery Level
table_lines.comment: A description of the camera’s battery level at the time of image capture, encoded as a decimal, ratio, or text string.

table_lines.name: Exposure Time in Seconds
table_lines.comment: Exposure time in seconds.

table_lines.name: F-Number
table_lines.comment: The f-number.

table_lines.name: OECF Rows
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO14524

table_lines.name: OECF Columns
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO14524

table_lines.name: OECF Column Names
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO14524

table_lines.name: OECF Values
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO14524

table_lines.name: Spatial Frequency Response Rows
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12233

table_lines.name: Spatial Frequency Response Columns
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12233

table_lines.name: Spatial Frequency Response Column Names
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12233

table_lines.name: Spatial Frequency Response Values
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12233

table_lines.name: Color Filter Array Pattern Rows
table_lines.comment: The number of rows in the color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern.

table_lines.name: Color Filter Array Pattern Columns
table_lines.comment: The number of columns in the color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern.

table_lines.name: Color Filter Array Pattern Values
table_lines.comment: The values of the color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern of the image sensor when a one-chip color area sensor is used, encoded as successive column values of the first row, then as successive column values of each successive row.

table_lines.name: Exposure Program
table_lines.comment: The class of the program used by the camera to set exposure.

table_lines.name: Spectral Sensitivity
table_lines.comment:
The spectral sensitivity of each channel of the camera used.
The value is an ASCII string compatible with the standard developed by the ASTM Technical Committee.

table_lines.name: Photographic Sensitivity
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: Sensitivity Type
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: Standard Output Sensitivity
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: Recommended Exposure Index
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: ISO Speed
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: ISO Speed Latitude yyy
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: ISO Speed Latitude zzz
table_lines.comment: biblio_ISO12232

table_lines.name: EXIF Version
table_lines.comment: The version of the EXIF standard.

table_lines.name: Shutter Speed Value
table_lines.comment: The shutter speed. The unit is the APEX value.

table_lines.name: Aperture Value
table_lines.comment: The lens aperture. The unit is the APEX value.

table_lines.name: Brightness Value
table_lines.comment: The value of brightness. The unit is the APEX value.

table_lines.name: Exposure Bias Value
table_lines.comment: The exposure bias. The unit is the APEX value.

table_lines.name: Max Aperture Value
table_lines.comment: The smallest F number of the lens. The unit is the APEX value.

table_lines.name: Subject Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance to the subject in meters.

table_lines.name: Metering Mode
table_lines.comment: The metering mode.

table_lines.name: Light Source
table_lines.comment: The kind of light source.

table_lines.name: Flash Firing Status
table_lines.comment: The status of firing of the flash (strobe light).

table_lines.name: Flash Return Status
table_lines.comment: The detection of returned light from firing of the flash (strobe light).

table_lines.name: Flash Mode
table_lines.comment: The camera's flash (strobe light) mode.

table_lines.name: Flash Function Present
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the camera has a flash function flash (strobe light).

table_lines.name: Flash Red Eye Mode
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the camera supports red-eye reduction.

table_lines.name: Focal Length
table_lines.comment: The actual focal length of the lens, in mm.

table_lines.name: Subject Area
table_lines.comment:
The location and area of the main subject in the overall scene.
If two values are present, they are the X and Y image-relative coordinates of a location.
If three values are present, they are the X and Y image-relative center coordinates and the diameter in pixels of a circle.
If four values are present, they are the center X image-relative coordinate, the center Y image-relative coordinate, the width in pixels, and the height in pixels of a rectangle.
The coordinate values, width, and height are expressed in relation to the upper left as origin.

table_lines.name: Maker Note
table_lines.comment: Any desired information. The contents are up to the manufacturer.

table_lines.name: Temperature
table_lines.comment: The ambient temperature at the time of acquisition, in °C.

table_lines.name: Humidity
table_lines.comment: The ambient humidity at the time of acquisition, in %.

table_lines.name: Pressure
table_lines.comment: The ambient pressure at the time of acquisition, in hPa.

table_lines.name: Water Depth
table_lines.comment:
The water depth at the time of acquisition, in m.
When the value is negative, the absolute value of it indicates the height (elevation) above the water level.

table_lines.name: Acceleration
table_lines.comment: The acceleration as a scalar, regardless of direction, at the time of acquisition, in mGal (10-5 m/s2).

table_lines.name: Camera Elevation Angle
table_lines.comment: The elevation/depression (angle of the orientation of the camera, imaging optical axis) in degrees from -180 to less than 180, at the time of acquisition.

table_lines.name: Flash Energy
table_lines.comment:
The amount of flash (strobe) energy at the time the image is captured, in Beam Candle Power Seconds (BCPS).
A single value if the exact flash energy is known, otherwise two values, the minimum value and the maximum value.

table_lines.name: Subject Location
table_lines.comment: The location of the main subject in the scene. The value of this tag represents the pixel at the center of the main subject relative to the upper left corner. The first value indicates the X column number and second indicates the Y row number.

table_lines.name: Photographic Exposure Index
table_lines.comment: The exposure index selected on the camera or input device at the time the image is captured.

table_lines.name: Sensing Method
table_lines.comment: The image sensor type on the camera or input device.

table_lines.name: File Source
table_lines.comment: The image source.

table_lines.name: Scene Type
table_lines.comment: The type of scene.

table_lines.name: Custom Rendered
table_lines.comment: Special processing that was used on image data.

table_lines.name: Exposure Mode
table_lines.comment: The exposure mode set when the image was shot.

table_lines.name: White Balance
table_lines.comment: The white balance mode set when the image was shot.

table_lines.name: Digital Zoom Ratio
table_lines.comment: The digital zoom ratio when the image was shot.

table_lines.name: Focal Length In 35mm Film
table_lines.comment: The equivalent focal length assuming a 35mm film camera, in mm.

table_lines.name: Scene Capture Type
table_lines.comment: The type of scene that was shot.

table_lines.name: Gain Control
table_lines.comment: The degree of overall image gain adjustment.

table_lines.name: Contrast
table_lines.comment: The direction of contrast processing applied by the camera.

table_lines.name: Saturation
table_lines.comment: The direction of saturation processing applied by the camera.

table_lines.name: Sharpness
table_lines.comment: The direction of sharpness processing applied by the camera.

table_lines.name: Device Setting Description
table_lines.comment: biblio_EXIF2.31

table_lines.name: Subject Distance Range
table_lines.comment: The distance to the subject.

table_lines.name: Self Timer Mode
table_lines.comment: The number of seconds the image capture was delayed from when the capture was initiated by the camera operator. If the value is zero, the self-timer is off.

table_lines.name: Interoperability Index
table_lines.comment: Identification of the interoperability rule to which the image conforms.

table_lines.name: Interoperability Version
table_lines.comment: The version interoperability rule to which the image conforms.

table_lines.name: GPS Version ID
table_lines.comment: The version of GPS information.

table_lines.name: GPS Latitude Ref
table_lines.comment: Whether the latitude is north or south latitude.

table_lines.name: GPS Latitude
table_lines.comment: The latitude, expressed as three non-negative values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively.

table_lines.name: GPS Longitude Ref
table_lines.comment: Whether the longitude is east or west longitude.

table_lines.name: GPS Longitude
table_lines.comment: The longitude, expressed as three non-negative values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively.

table_lines.name: GPS Altitude Ref
table_lines.comment:
The altitude used as the reference altitude in meters.
If the reference is sea level and the altitude is above sea level, 0 is given. If the altitude is below sea level, a value of 1 is given and the altitude is indicated as an absolute value in GPS Altitude (0016,0076).

table_lines.name: GPS Altitude
table_lines.comment: The altitude based on the reference in GPS Altitude Ref (0016,0075), in meters.

table_lines.name: GPS Time Stamp
table_lines.comment: The time as UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).

table_lines.name: GPS Satellites
table_lines.comment: The GPS satellites used for measurements. This tag can be used to describe the number of satellites, their ID number, angle of elevation, azimuth, SNR and other information. The format is not specified.

table_lines.name: GPS Status
table_lines.comment: The status of the GPS receiver when the image is recorded.

table_lines.name: GPS Measure Mode
table_lines.comment: The GPS measurement mode.

table_lines.name: GPS DOP
table_lines.comment:
The GPS data degree (dilution) of precision.
A horizontal dilution of precision (HDOP) value is written during two-dimensional measurement, and position (3D) dilution of precision (PDOP) during three-dimensional measurement.

table_lines.name: GPS Speed Ref
table_lines.comment: The unit used to express the GPS Speed (0016,007D).

table_lines.name: GPS Speed
table_lines.comment: The speed of GPS receiver movement in GPS Speed Ref (0016,007C) units.

table_lines.name: GPS Track Ref
table_lines.comment: The reference for giving the direction of GPS receiver movement.

table_lines.name: GPS Track
table_lines.comment: The direction of GPS receiver movement in degrees. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

table_lines.name: GPS Img Direction Ref
table_lines.comment: The reference for giving the direction of the image when it is captured.

table_lines.name: GPS Img Direction
table_lines.comment: The direction of the image when it was captured. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

table_lines.name: GPS Map Datum
table_lines.comment: The geodetic survey data used by the GPS receiver.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Latitude Ref
table_lines.comment: Whether the latitude of the destination point is north or south latitude.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Latitude
table_lines.comment: The latitude of the destination point. The latitude is expressed as three values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Longitude Ref
table_lines.comment: Whether the longitude of the destination point is east or west longitude.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Longitude
table_lines.comment: The longitude of the destination point. The longitude is expressed as three values giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Bearing Ref
table_lines.comment: Indicates the reference used for giving the bearing to the destination point.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Bearing
table_lines.comment: The bearing to the destination point in degrees. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Distance Ref
table_lines.comment: The unit used to express the distance to the destination point.

table_lines.name: GPS Dest Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance to the destination point in GPS Dest Distance Ref (0016,0089) units.

table_lines.name: GPS Processing Method
table_lines.comment: The name of the method used for location finding.

table_lines.name: GPS Area Information
table_lines.comment: The name of the GPS area.

table_lines.name: GPS Date Stamp
table_lines.comment: The date and time information relative to UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).

table_lines.name: GPS Differential
table_lines.comment: Whether differential correction is applied to the GPS receiver.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the Patient.
The value of Recognizable Visual Features (0028,0302) shall be YES if the image contains the patient's fingerprints

table_lines.name: Light Source Polarization
table_lines.comment: Polarization of the dermoscope light source.

table_lines.name: Emitter Color Temperature
table_lines.comment: Color temperature of dermoscope light source in Kelvin.

table_lines.name: Contact Method
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the image was acquired with the dermoscope in direct contact with the skin.

table_lines.name: Immersion Media
table_lines.comment:
The interface between the dermoscope and the skin surface for images acquired with contact dermoscopy.
Required if Contact Method (0016,1003) is CONTACT

table_lines.name: Optical Magnification Factor
table_lines.comment:
n
Optical magnification factor when the image was acquired.
                                        Optical magnification is achieved using the optics of the dermoscope.
                                        The number indicates the magnification factor in times (X).
                                        The size of an object (e.g., a skin lesion) would appear on the sensor

table_lines.name: Partial View
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether this image is a partial view, that is a subset of a single view of a skin lesion.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not be a partial view.

table_lines.name: Partial View Description
table_lines.comment: Free text description of the portion of the skin lesion captured in a partial view image.

table_lines.name: Tracking ID
table_lines.comment:
A text label used for tracking a finding or feature, potentially across multiple reporting objects, over time.
                                        This label shall be unique within the domain in which it is used.
Required if Tracking UID (0062,0021) is present.

table_lines.name: Tracking UID
table_lines.comment:
A unique identifier used for tracking a finding or feature, potentially across multiple reporting objects, over time.
Required if Tracking ID (0062,0020) is present.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit. Shall be one less than the value in Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Burned In Annotation
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the image was acquired.
This means that images that contain this Module shall not contain such burned in annotations.
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment:
Specifies an identity transformation for the Presentation LUT, such that the output of all grayscale transformations defined in the IOD containing this Module are defined to be P-Values.
Required if Photometric Interpretation (0028,0004) is MONOCHROME2.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the Image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

C.8-83.table_caption: MR Image and Spectroscopy Instance Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Acquisition Number
table_lines.comment: A number identifying the single continuous gathering of data over a period of time that resulted in this image.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment:
The date and time that the acquisition of data started.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator
See
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Resonant Nucleus
table_lines.comment:
Nucleus that is resonant at the transmitter frequency.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: k-space Filtering
table_lines.comment:
Describes k-space filtering applied. Shall be NONE if no k-space filter.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Magnetic Field Strength
table_lines.comment:
Nominal field strength of the MR Magnet, in Tesla.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Applicable Safety Standard Agency
table_lines.comment:
Agency that established MR safety standard applicable to the acquisition of this Instance.
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Applicable Safety Standard Description
table_lines.comment: Name and Version of the applicable standard.

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about the image.

table_lines.name: Isocenter Position
table_lines.comment: Isocenter coordinates (x,y,z), in mm. Specifies the location of the machine isocenter in the Patient-Based Coordinate System associated with the Frame of Reference. It allows transformation from the Equipment-Based Coordinate System to the Patient-Based Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: B1rms
table_lines.comment: biblio_IEC60601-2-33

table_lines.name: Complex Image Component
table_lines.comment: Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Contrast
table_lines.comment: Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Functional Settling Phase Frames Present
table_lines.comment: Specifies if the acquisition used and stored settling phases.

table_lines.name: Pulse Sequence Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of the pulse sequence for annotation purposes. Potentially vendor-specific name.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Acquisition Type
table_lines.comment:
Identification of spatial data encoding scheme.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Echo Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Echo category of pulse sequences.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Multiple Spin Echo
table_lines.comment:
Multiple Spin Echo category of pulse sequence used to collect different lines in k-space for a single frame.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals SPIN or BOTH.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals SPIN or BOTH.

table_lines.name: Multi-planar Excitation
table_lines.comment:
Technique that simultaneously excites several volumes.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Phase Contrast
table_lines.comment:
Phase contrast pulse sequence is a pulse sequence in which the flowing spins are velocity encoded in phase.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Velocity Encoding Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Velocity encoding directions used for acquisition.
Required if Phase Contrast (0018,9014) equals YES.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Time of Flight Contrast
table_lines.comment:
Time of Flight contrast is created by the inflow of blood in the saturated plane.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Arterial Spin Labeling Contrast
table_lines.comment:
Arterial Spin Labeling contrast technique.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 3 is ASL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Steady State Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Steady State Sequence.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Echo Planar Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Echo Planar category of Pulse Sequences.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Saturation Recovery
table_lines.comment:
Saturation recovery pulse sequence.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Spectrally Selected Suppression
table_lines.comment:
Spectrally Selected Suppression.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Oversampling Phase
table_lines.comment:
Oversampling Phase.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Geometry of k-Space Traversal
table_lines.comment:
Geometry category of k-Space traversal.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Rectilinear Phase Encode Reordering
table_lines.comment:
Rectilinear phase encode reordering.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and Geometry of k-Space Traversal (0018,9032) equals RECTILINEAR.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and Geometry of k-Space Traversal (0018,9032) equals RECTILINEAR.

table_lines.name: Segmented k-Space Traversal
table_lines.comment:
Segmented k-Space traversal. If Geometry of k-Space Traversal is rectilinear, multiple lines can be acquired at one time. If Geometry of k-Space Traversal is spiral or radial, paths can be interleaved and acquired at one time.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Coverage of k-Space
table_lines.comment:
Coverage of k-Space in the ky-kz plane.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and MR Acquisition Type (0018,0023) equals 3D.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and MR Acquisition Type (0018,0023) equals 3D.

table_lines.name: Number of k-Space Trajectories
table_lines.comment:
Number of interleaves or shots.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

C.8-88.table_caption: MR Image Frame Type Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: MR Image Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008), except that the value MIXED is not allowed unless the SOP Class UID is "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.4.4" (Legacy Converted). See

C.8-89.table_caption: MR Timing and Related Parameters Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: MR Timing and Related Parameters Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the timing and safety information of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Repetition Time
table_lines.comment:
The time in ms between two successive excitations of the same volume. Shall be 0 (zero) if there is a single excitation per volume.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Flip Angle
table_lines.comment:
Steady state angle in degrees to which the magnetic vector is flipped from the magnetic vector of the primary field.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Echo Train Length
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >RF Echo Train Length
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Gradient Echo Train Length
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Specific Absorption Rate Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the methods of SAR calculation and the corresponding values.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the system is capable of calculating Specific Absorption Rate (0018,9181).

table_lines.name: >>Specific Absorption Rate Definition
table_lines.comment: Specification of the method of SAR calculation as defined in Applicable Safety Standard Description (0018,9175).

table_lines.name: >>Specific Absorption Rate Value
table_lines.comment: Specific Absorption Rate in W/kg.

table_lines.name: >Gradient Output Type
table_lines.comment:
Definition of gradient output unit, for which the value is stored in Gradient Output (0018,9182).
Required if the system is capable of calculating Gradient Output (0018,9182).

table_lines.name: >Gradient Output
table_lines.comment:
Unit is defined by Gradient Output Type (0018,9180).
Required if the system is capable of calculating Gradient Output (0018,9182).

table_lines.name: >Operating Mode Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of operating mode information relating to the Frame/SOP Instance as required to adhere to the Applicable Safety Standard Agency (0018,9174) regulations.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if required by law or regulations. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Operating Mode
table_lines.comment: Operating mode applicable for the defined by the applicable standard.

table_lines.name: MR FOV/Geometry Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the geometry parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >In-plane Phase Encoding Direction
table_lines.comment:
The axes of the in-plane phase encoding with respect to the frame.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >MR Acquisition Frequency Encoding Steps
table_lines.comment:
Number of Frequency Encoding steps (kx) acquired
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >MR Acquisition Phase Encoding Steps in-plane
table_lines.comment:
Number of In-Plane Phase Encoding steps (ky) acquired
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >MR Acquisition Phase Encoding Steps out-of-plane
table_lines.comment:
Number of Out-of-Plane Phase Encoding steps (kz) acquired
Required if MR Acquisition Type (0018,0023) equals 3D and Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Percent Sampling
table_lines.comment:
Fraction of acquisition matrix lines acquired, expressed as a percent.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Percent Phase Field of View
table_lines.comment:
Ratio of field of view dimension in phase direction to field of view dimension in frequency direction, expressed as a percent.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Echo Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies echo timing of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Effective Echo Time
table_lines.comment:
The time in ms between the middle of the excitation pulse and the peak of the echo produced for kx=0.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Modifier Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies general acquisition parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Inversion Recovery
table_lines.comment:
Inversion Recovery preparatory sequence.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Inversion Times
table_lines.comment:
Times in ms after the middle of inverting RF pulse to middle of excitation pulse to detect the amount of longitudinal magnetization.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Inversion Recovery (0018,9009) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Inversion Recovery (0018,9009) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Flow Compensation
table_lines.comment:
Flow Compensation.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Flow Compensation Direction
table_lines.comment:
Flow Compensation Direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Flow Compensation (0018,9010) equals other than NONE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Flow Compensation (0018,9010) equals other than NONE.

table_lines.name: >Spoiling
table_lines.comment:
Spoiling.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals GRADIENT or BOTH.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals GRADIENT or BOTH.

table_lines.name: >T2 Preparation
table_lines.comment:
T2 prepared Pulse Sequence.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Spectrally Selected Excitation
table_lines.comment:
Spectrally Selected Excitation.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Spatial Pre-saturation
table_lines.comment:
Spatial Pre-saturation.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Partial Fourier
table_lines.comment:
Partial Fourier.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Partial Fourier Direction
table_lines.comment:
Direction of Partial Fourier.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Partial Fourier (0018,9081) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Partial Fourier (0018,9081) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Parallel Acquisition
table_lines.comment:
Parallel acquisition has been used to reduce measurement time.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Parallel Acquisition Technique
table_lines.comment:
Parallel acquisition characteristics.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Parallel Reduction Factor In-plane
table_lines.comment:
Measurement time reduction factor expressed as ratio of original and reduced measurement time for the in-plane direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Parallel Reduction Factor out-of-plane
table_lines.comment:
Measurement time reduction factor expressed as ratio of original and reduced measurement time for the out-of-plane direction
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Parallel Reduction Factor Second In-plane
table_lines.comment:
Measurement time reduction factor expressed as ratio of original and reduced measurement time for the second in-plane direction.
Only required for MR Spectroscopy SOP Instances.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Parallel Acquisition (0018,9077) equals YES.

table_lines.name: MR Imaging Modifier Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence containing MR modifier Sequence Attributes.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Magnetization Transfer
table_lines.comment:
Magnetization Transfer pulse sequence.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Blood Signal Nulling
table_lines.comment:
Blood Signal Nulling ("Black Blood") preparatory pulse sequence.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Tagging
table_lines.comment:
Tagging.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Tag Spacing First Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Space between lines in mm.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.

table_lines.name: >Tag Spacing Second Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Space between the lines in mm in the other direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID.

table_lines.name: >Tag Angle First Axis
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the tag lines relative to the rows axis (left to right) of the image, with a range of 0-180 degrees. The angle is increasing in clockwise direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.

table_lines.name: >Tag Angle Second Axis
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the tag lines relative to the rows axis (left to right) of the image, with a range of 0-180 degrees. The angle is increasing in clockwise direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID.

table_lines.name: >Tag Thickness
table_lines.comment:
Thickness of the line in mm.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is DERIVED and Tagging (0018,9028) is GRID or LINE.

table_lines.name: >Tagging Delay
table_lines.comment: Delay time in ms of the beginning of the application of the tagging pattern relative to the last R-peak.

table_lines.name: >Transmitter Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Center transmitter frequency in MHz.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Pixel Bandwidth
table_lines.comment:
Reciprocal of the effective sampling period, in hertz per pixel.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Receive Coil Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides information about each receive coil used.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Receive Coil Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of receive coil used.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Receive Coil Manufacturer Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of manufacturer of receive coil.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Receive Coil Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of receive coil used.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Quadrature Receive Coil
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether the receive coil is quadrature.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Multi-Coil Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides information regarding each element of a multi-coil. It should include Attributes for all elements, whether used in the current acquisition or not. One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Receive Coil Type (0018,9043) equals MULTICOIL. May be present otherwise only if Receive Coil Type (0018,9043) equals MULTICOIL.

table_lines.name: >>Multi-Coil Element Name
table_lines.comment: Name of element of multi-coil.

table_lines.name: >>Multi-Coil Element Used
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether the multi-coil element was used in the current acquisition.

table_lines.name: >Multi-Coil Configuration
table_lines.comment: A textual description of the configuration of multi-coil elements that was used in the current acquisition.

table_lines.name: MR Transmit Coil Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides information about the transmit coil used.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Transmit Coil Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of transmit coil used.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Transmit Coil Manufacturer Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of manufacturer of transmit coil.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Transmit Coil Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of transmit coil used.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Diffusion Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the diffusion parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Diffusion b-value
table_lines.comment:
Diffusion sensitization factor in sec/mm
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Diffusion Directionality
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether diffusion conditions for the frame are directional, or isotropic with respect to direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Diffusion Gradient Direction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing orientations of all diffusion sensitization gradients that were applied during the acquisition of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Diffusion Directionality (0018,9075) equals DIRECTIONAL
May be present if Diffusion Directionality (0018,9075) equals BMATRIX.

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion Gradient Orientation
table_lines.comment:
The direction cosines of the diffusion gradient vector with respect to the patient
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Diffusion b-matrix Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The directional diffusion sensitization expressed as a 3x3 matrix with diagonal symmetry (with six unique elements from which the other elements can be derived).
The rows and columns of the matrix are the X (right to left), Y (anterior to posterior) and Z (foot to head) patient-relative orthogonal axes as defined in
The values are in units of ms/mm
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Diffusion Directionality (0018,9075) equals BMATRIX.

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value XX
table_lines.comment: The value of b[X,X].

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value XY
table_lines.comment: The value of b[X,Y].

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value XZ
table_lines.comment: The value of b[X,Z].

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value YY
table_lines.comment: The value of b[Y,Y].

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value YZ
table_lines.comment: The value of b[Y,Z].

table_lines.name: >>Diffusion b-value ZZ
table_lines.comment: The value of b[Z,Z].

table_lines.name: >Diffusion Anisotropy Type
table_lines.comment:
Class of diffusion anisotropy calculation.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) value 4 equals DIFFUSION_ANISO.

table_lines.name: MR Averages Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the averaging parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Number of Averages
table_lines.comment:
Maximum number of times any point in k-space is acquired.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Spatial Saturation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides the position of spatial saturation bands deposited as part of the pulse sequence.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Slab Thickness
table_lines.comment: Thickness of slab in mm.

table_lines.name: MR Metabolite Map Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the chemical shift parameters used to measure the resonant peaks from which the MR metabolite map represented by this frame was derived.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Metabolite Map Description
table_lines.comment:
Text describing the Metabolite Map.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Metabolite Map Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
When the measured peaks or their ratios can be related to metabolite substances, this Sequence may be used to describe the metabolite substance whose resonant peaks are mapped in the Metabolite Map, or the ratio of substance resonant peaks that is mapped.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Chemical Shift Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The list of frequencies that were used to create the Metabolite Map.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Chemical Shift Minimum Integration Limit in ppm
table_lines.comment: Minimal value of Chemical Shift Frequency in ppm.

table_lines.name: >>Chemical Shift Maximum Integration Limit in ppm
table_lines.comment: Maximum value of Chemical Shift Frequency in ppm.

table_lines.name: MR Velocity Encoding Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the velocity encoding of this frame.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Velocity Encoding Direction
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Velocity Encoding Minimum Value
table_lines.comment:
Minimum velocity in cm/s.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Velocity Encoding Maximum Value
table_lines.comment:
Maximum velocity in cm/s.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

C.8-100b.table_caption: MR Arterial Spin Labeling Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: MR Arterial Spin Labeling Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides the position of Arterial Spin Labeling regions deposited as part of the pulse sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >ASL Technique Description
table_lines.comment: Text describing the used labeling technique in more detail.

table_lines.name: >ASL Context
table_lines.comment:
The purpose of the Arterial Spin Labeling.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.
See

table_lines.name: >ASL Slab Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence describing the ASL Slab geometry and anatomical region.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if ASL Context (0018,9257) is CONTROL or LABEL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>ASL Slab Number
table_lines.comment: Consecutive number identifying the different slabs used for labeling, starting with 1.

table_lines.usage:
The anatomical region where the slab is positioned.

Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) D

Anatomic Region Modifier Sequence (0008,2220) and Primary Anatomic Structure Modifier Sequence (0008,2230) D

table_lines.name: >>ASL Slab Thickness
table_lines.comment: Thickness of slab in mm.

table_lines.name: >>ASL Pulse Train Duration
table_lines.comment:
Duration (in milliseconds) of the Label or Control pulse.
See

table_lines.name: >ASL Crusher Flag
table_lines.comment:
Indicates if an ASL Crusher Method has been used.
See

table_lines.name: >ASL Crusher Flow Limit
table_lines.comment:
Maximum Flow Limit (in cm/s).
Required if ASL Crusher Flag (0018,9259) is YES.

table_lines.name: >ASL Crusher Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the ASL Crusher Method. Required if ASL Crusher Flag (0018,9259) is YES.

table_lines.name: >ASL Bolus Cut-off Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates if a Bolus Cut-off technique is used.

table_lines.name: >ASL Bolus Cut-off Timing Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that specifies the timing of the Bolus Cut-off technique and possibly its (scientific) description.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if ASL Bolus Cut-off Flag (0018,925C) is YES.

table_lines.name: >>ASL Bolus Cut-off Delay Time
table_lines.comment:
Bolus Cut-off pulse delay time (in ms).
See

table_lines.name: >>ASL Bolus Cut-off Technique
table_lines.comment: Text describing the cut-off technique.

table_lines.name: Functional MR Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the Functional parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Settling Phase Frame
table_lines.comment:
Identifies if the frame is part of a Functional MR settling phase. All frames with the same combination of Stack ID (0020,9056) and Temporal Position Index (0020,9128) shall have the same value.
Required if Functional Settling Phase Frames Present (0018,9622) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Functional Sync Pulse
table_lines.comment:
The date and time of the Functional Sync Pulse for this frame.
See

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the images in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Transmitter Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Precession frequency in MHz of the nucleus being addressed for each spectral axis.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Spectral Width
table_lines.comment:
Spectral width in Hz.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Chemical Shift Reference

The chemical shift at the transmitter frequency in ppm.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Volume Localization Technique
table_lines.comment:
Name of volume localization technique used. Shall be "NONE" if no spatial localization was performed.
