table_lines.name: Volume Localization Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items that provide the position of RF excitations used to select a volume of tissue. The selected volume is described by the intersection of the Sequence Items.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and Volume Localization Technique (0018,9054) is other than NONE. May be present if Volume Localization Technique (0018,9054) is other than NONE.

table_lines.name: >Slab Thickness
table_lines.comment: Thickness of slab in mm.

table_lines.name: De-coupling
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether de-coupling was active.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: De-coupled Nucleus
table_lines.comment:
Nucleus being de-coupled.
See
Required if De-coupling (0018,9059) equals YES.

table_lines.name: De-coupling Frequency
table_lines.comment:
The center frequency (Hz) for the de-coupling.
See
Required if De-coupling (0018,9059) equals YES.

table_lines.name: De-coupling Method
table_lines.comment:
The de-coupling modulation scheme used.
Required if De-coupling (0018,9059) equals YES.

table_lines.name: De-coupling Chemical Shift Reference
table_lines.comment:
The chemical shift in ppm at the de-coupling frequency.
See
Required if De-coupling (0018,9059) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Time Domain Filtering
table_lines.comment:
Describes time domain filtering or apodization applied. Shall be NONE if no filtering operations were applied to the time domain data.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Number of Zero Fills
table_lines.comment:
Number of zero fills added to the time domain data before FT. Shall be 0 (zero) if no zero filling performed.
See
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Baseline Correction
table_lines.comment:
Describes baseline correction techniques. Shall be NONE if no baseline correction was performed.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Frequency Correction
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether operations were performed to correct resonant frequency of metabolite peaks due to B0 field inhomogeneities.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: First Order Phase Correction
table_lines.comment:
Describes whether a first order (frequency dependent) phase correction was applied to the spectral data.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Water Referenced Phase Correction
table_lines.comment:
Indicates if the images or spectra were created using Water Reference time domain data for phase correction.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.
See

table_lines.name: Water Reference Acquisition
table_lines.comment:
Describes the relation to Water Reference data for this Instance.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
References to SOP Instances significantly related to the current SOP Instance, including water reference data.
Required if Water Reference Acquisition (0018,9297) equals REFERENCED. May be present otherwise.
One or more Items shall be present in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.

C.8-103.table_caption: MR Spectroscopy Pulse Sequence Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Pulse Sequence Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of the pulse sequence for annotation purposes. Potentially vendor-specific name.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: MR Spectroscopy Acquisition Type
table_lines.comment:
Identification of data encoding scheme.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Echo Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Echo category of pulse sequences.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Multiple Spin Echo
table_lines.comment:
Multiple Spin Echo category of pulse sequence used to collect different lines in k-space for a single frame.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals SPIN or BOTH.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and Echo Pulse Sequence (0018,9008) equals SPIN or BOTH.

table_lines.name: Multi-planar Excitation
table_lines.comment:
Technique that simultaneously excites several volumes.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Steady State Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Steady State Sequence.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Echo Planar Pulse Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Echo Planar category of pulse sequences.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Spectrally Selected Suppression
table_lines.comment:
Spectrally Selected Suppression.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Geometry of k-Space Traversal
table_lines.comment:
Geometry category of k-Space traversal.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Rectilinear Phase Encode Reordering
table_lines.comment:
Rectilinear phase encode reordering.
Required if Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and Geometry of k-Space Traversal (0018,9032) equals RECTILINEAR.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and Geometry of k-Space Traversal (0018,9032) equals RECTILINEAR.

table_lines.name: Segmented k-Space Traversal
table_lines.comment:
Segmented k-Space traversal. If Geometry of k-Space Traversal is rectilinear, multiple lines can be acquired at one time. If Geometry of k-Space Traversal is spiral or radial, paths can be interleaved and acquired at one time.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Coverage of k-Space
table_lines.comment:
Coverage of k-Space.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED and MR Spectroscopy Acquisition Type (0018,9200) equals VOLUME.
Otherwise may be present if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and MR Spectroscopy Acquisition Type (0018,9200) equals VOLUME.

table_lines.name: Number of k-Space Trajectories
table_lines.comment:
Number of interleaves or shots.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL or MIXED. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Echo Peak Position
table_lines.comment: Number specifying the sample that coincides with the echo peak used during acquisition of the data. First sample will be numbered 1.

C.8-104.table_caption: MR Spectroscopy Frame Type Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: MR Spectroscopy Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence containing Frame Type Attributes.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: MR Spectroscopy FOV/Geometry Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the geometry parameters of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Spectroscopy Acquisition Data Columns
table_lines.comment:
Number of data points in the columns direction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Spectroscopy Acquisition Phase Rows
table_lines.comment:
Number of Phase Encoding Rows.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Spectroscopy Acquisition Phase Columns
table_lines.comment:
Number of Phase Encoding Columns.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Spectroscopy Acquisition Out-of-plane Phase Steps
table_lines.comment:
Number of out-of-plane Phase Encoding steps.
Required if MR Spectroscopy Acquisition Type (0018,9200) equals PLANE and Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Percent Sampling
table_lines.comment:
Fraction of acquisition matrix lines acquired, expressed as a percent.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Percent Phase Field of View
table_lines.comment:
Ratio of field of view dimension in phase direction to field of view dimension in frequency direction, expressed as a percent.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of voxels in the vertical direction in the frame.

table_lines.name: Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of voxels in the horizontal direction in the frame.

table_lines.name: Data Point Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of rows of data points in spectroscopic data.

table_lines.name: Data Point Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of columns of data points in spectroscopic data.

table_lines.name: Data Representation
table_lines.comment: Data representation of the data points. Each data point shall have the same representation.

table_lines.name: Signal Domain Columns
table_lines.comment: Domain of represented signal in column direction.

table_lines.name: Signal Domain Rows
table_lines.comment:
Domain of represented signal in row direction.
Required if Data Point Rows (0028,9001) has a value of more than 1.

table_lines.name: First Order Phase Correction Angle
table_lines.comment:
First Order Phase Correction Angle. Number of values is determined by Row*Column*Number of Frames.
Required if First Order Phase Correction (0018,9198) equals YES

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the images in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Multi-energy CT Acquisition
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether the image is created by means of Multi-energy technique.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Number
table_lines.comment: A number identifying the single continuous gathering of data over a period of time that resulted in this image.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment:
The date and time that the acquisition of data started.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or MIXED and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples (planes) in this image. This value shall be 1.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the intended interpretation of the pixel data.
See

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits allocated. This value shall be 16.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits stored. This value shall be 12 or16.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit. Shall be one less than the value in Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator
See
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about the image

table_lines.name: Burned In Annotation
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the image was acquired.
This means that images that contain this Module shall not contain such burned in annotations.
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment: Specifies an identity transformation for the Presentation LUT, such that the output of all grayscale transformations defined in the IOD containing this Module are defined to be P-Values.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the Image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Isocenter Position
table_lines.comment: Isocenter coordinates (x,y,z), in mm. Specifies the location of the machine isocenter in the Patient-Based Coordinate System associated with the Frame of Reference. It allows transformation from the Equipment-Based Coordinate System to the Patient-Based Coordinate System.

C.8-117.table_caption: CT Image Frame Type Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: CT Image Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008), except that the value MIXED is not allowed unless the SOP Class UID is "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2.2" (Legacy Converted). See

table_lines.name: CT Acquisition Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the CT acquisition mode.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Type
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Tube Angle
table_lines.comment:
The constant angle at which the X-Ray source is located during acquisition. 0 degrees means that the source is located at the highest point of the gantry orbit. Degrees increase from 0 to positive 360 in a clockwise direction as viewed when facing the gantry where the table enters the gantry.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is CONSTANT_ANGLE.
May be present otherwise if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Constant Volume Flag
table_lines.comment:
Identifies that the acquisition was performed by repetitively acquiring the same volume set over a period of time.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Fluoroscopy Flag
table_lines.comment:
Identifies that near real-time display of a block of continuously acquired data was performed, which may result in a lower than usual image quality.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: CT Acquisition Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the details of the acquisition.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is NO or is absent, only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is YES, one or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Path Index
table_lines.comment:
References the X-Ray Path Index (0018,937A) in the Multi-energy CT Path Sequence (0018,9379) for this exposure.
Required if Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Rotation Direction
table_lines.comment:
Direction of rotation of the source about the gantry, as viewed while facing the gantry where the table enters the gantry.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL, and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is other than CONSTANT_ANGLE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED, and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is other than CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Revolution Time
table_lines.comment:
The time in seconds of a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit. This value is independent of the Reconstruction Angle (0018,9319) of the frame.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL, and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is other than CONSTANT_ANGLE.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED, and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is other than CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Single Collimation Width
table_lines.comment:
The width of a single row of acquired data (in mm).
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Total Collimation Width
table_lines.comment:
The width of the total collimation (in mm) over the area of active X-Ray detection.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Table Height
table_lines.comment:
The distance in mm from the top of the patient table to the center of rotation of the source (i.e., the data collection center or isocenter). The distance is positive when the table is below the data collection center.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Gantry/Detector Tilt
table_lines.comment:
Nominal angle of tilt in degrees of the scanning gantry. Not intended for mathematical computations. Zero degrees means the gantry is not tilted, negative degrees are when the top of the gantry is tilted away from where the table enters the gantry.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Data Collection Diameter
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: CT Table Dynamics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the movement of the CT table.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Speed
table_lines.comment:
The distance in mm that the table moves in one second during the gathering of data that resulted in this frame.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL or CONSTANT_ANGLE.
May be present otherwise if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL or CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Table Feed per Rotation
table_lines.comment:
Motion of the table (in mm) during a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL.
May be present otherwise if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL.

table_lines.name: >Spiral Pitch Factor
table_lines.comment:
Ratio of the Table Feed per Rotation (0018,9310) to the Total Collimation Width (0018,9307).
See
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL.
May be present otherwise if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is SPIRAL.

table_lines.name: CT Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the CT geometry.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Position
table_lines.comment:
Relative longitudinal position of acquisition location of this frame in mm from an implementation specific reference point. Shall be relative to the same reference point for all frames in this SOP Instance, but may be different from the reference point in other SOP Instances. Positions as the table moves into the gantry viewed from the front are more negative.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Data Collection Center (Patient)
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Target Center (Patient)
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: CT Geometry Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the CT geometry.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is NO or is absent, only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is YES, one or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Path Index
table_lines.comment:
References the X-Ray Path Index (0018,937A) in the Multi-energy CT Path Sequence (0018,9379) for this exposure.
Required if Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Data Collection Center
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL or Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: CT Reconstruction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes holding information about the reconstruction techniques used.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Algorithm
table_lines.comment:
Description of the algorithm used when reconstructing the image from the data acquired during the acquisition process.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Convolution Kernel
table_lines.comment:
A label describing the convolution kernel or algorithm used to reconstruct the data. A single value shall be present.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Convolution Kernel Group
table_lines.comment:
A label describing the group to which Convolution Kernel (0018,1210).
Required if Convolution Kernel (0018,1210) is present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Diameter
table_lines.comment:
The diameter defines a circular region that is entirely contained within the encoded Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), unless the encoded image has been cropped after reconstruction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Reconstruction Field of View (0018,9317) is not present.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Reconstruction Field of View (0018,9317) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Field of View
table_lines.comment:
The field of view width followed by height as used for reconstruction in mm.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) is not present.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is DERIVED and Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Pixel Spacing
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle (in degrees) over which the data from which the frame was reconstructed was collected, where 360 degrees signifies a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit. It is possible, in the case of over-scanning that the Reconstruction Angle is greater than 360 degrees.
Shall be 0 if Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is CONSTANT_ANGLE.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Image Filter
table_lines.comment:
A label describing the filter applied to the reconstructed image after the original reconstruction has been completed.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL.

table_lines.name: CT Exposure Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining exposure information.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is NO or is absent, only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
If Multi-energy CT Acquisition (0018,9361) is YES, one or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced X-Ray Source Index
table_lines.comment:
References the X-Ray Source Index (0018,9366) in the Multi-energy CT Source Sequence (0018,9365) for which exposure details are specified here.

table_lines.name: >Exposure Time in ms

Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the values of Image Type (0008,0008).
See

table_lines.name: >Pixel Intensity Relationship Sign
table_lines.comment:
The sign of the relationship between the Pixel sample values stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) and the X-Ray beam intensity.
See

table_lines.name: >Imager Pixel Spacing
table_lines.comment:
The value of this Attribute shall never be adjusted to account for calibration against an object of known size; Pixel Spacing (0028,0030) is specified for that purpose.
It is only allowed to be adjusted to compensate for the change of the Field of View Dimension(s) in Float (0018,9461) Attribute. See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Pixel Data Area Origin Relative To FOV
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the TLHC of the image stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) from the TLHC of the Field Of View Area after FOV rotation and Flip. It is measured in image stored pixels as a row offset followed by a column offset.
See

table_lines.name: >Pixel Data Area Rotation Angle Relative To FOV
table_lines.comment:
Angle clockwise of the row direction of the image stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) relative to the row direction of the Field Of View Area after FOV rotation and Flip. It is measured in degrees.
See

table_lines.name: >Geometrical Properties
table_lines.comment: Geometrical characteristics of the pixel data to indicate whether pixel spacing is uniform for all pixels or not.

table_lines.name: >Geometric Maximum Distortion
table_lines.comment:
The percentage of the maximum deviation of the pixel spacing values of images for which the geometric properties are non-uniform.
Required if Geometrical Properties (0028,9444) equals NON_UNIFORM.

table_lines.name: >Image Processing Applied
table_lines.comment: The type or a combination of types of image processing applied to the pixel data before being stored.

C.8.19.6-5.table_caption: X-Ray Frame Detector Parameters Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Frame Detector Parameters Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the detector properties for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Detector Active Time
table_lines.comment: Time in mSec that the detector is active during acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: >Detector Activation Offset From Exposure
table_lines.comment: Offset time in mSec that the detector becomes active after the X-Ray beam is turned on during acquisition of this image. May be negative.

C.8.19.6-6.table_caption: X-Ray Calibration Device Usage Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Calibration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the calibration flag for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Calibration Image
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether a reference object (phantom) of known size is present in the frame and was used for calibration.

table_lines.name: Object Thickness Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing object thickness for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Calculated Anatomy Thickness
table_lines.comment: The physical thickness in mm of the anatomic region of interest as specified in the Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) in the direction of the center of the beam.

table_lines.name: Frame Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the acquisition parameters for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >KVP
table_lines.comment: Exact peak kilo voltage output of the X-Ray generator used for this frame.

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment: Exact Nominal X-Ray tube current in milliamperes applied during Acquisition Duration (0018,9220) for this frame.

C.8.19.6-9.table_caption: X-Ray Projection Pixel Calibration Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Projection Pixel Calibration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the geometrical position of the patient relative to the equipment.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Distance Object to Table Top
table_lines.comment: Distance between the anatomic region of interest of observation and table top in mm.

table_lines.name: >Object Pixel Spacing in Center of Beam
table_lines.comment: Required if Distance Object to Table Top (0018,9403) is not empty.

table_lines.name: >Table Height
table_lines.comment:
The distance of the top of the patient table to the center of rotation of the source (i.e., the isocenter) in mm. A positive value indicates that the tabletop is below the isocenter.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Beam Angle
table_lines.comment:
The equipment related angle in degrees of the X-Ray beam relative to the perpendicular to the tabletop plane. An angle from 0 to +90 degrees indicates that the X-Ray source is below the table.
The valid range is 0 to +180 degrees.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Positioner Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the geometrical position of the positioner.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray Image Intensifier about the patient from the RAO to LAO direction where movement from RAO to vertical is positive.
See
Required if Positioner Type (0018,1508) equals CARM.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray Image Intensifier about the patient from the CAU to CRA direction where movement from CAU to vertical is positive.
See
Required if Positioner Type (0018,1508) equals CARM.

table_lines.name: >Column Angulation (Patient)
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in degree relative to an orthogonal axis to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the tilt is towards the head of the patient.
Required if Positioner Type (0018,1508) equals COLUMN.

table_lines.name: Table Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the geometrical position of the table top.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Top Vertical Position
table_lines.comment: Table Top Vertical position with respect to an arbitrary chosen reference by the equipment in (mm). Table motion downwards is positive

table_lines.name: >Table Top Longitudinal Position
table_lines.comment: Table Top Longitudinal position with respect to an arbitrary chosen reference by the equipment in (mm). Table motion towards LAO is positive assuming that the patient is positioned supine and its head is in normal position.

table_lines.name: >Table Top Lateral Position
table_lines.comment: Table Top Lateral position with respect to an arbitrary chosen reference by the equipment in (mm). Table motion towards CRA is positive assuming that the patient is positioned supine and its head is in normal position.

table_lines.name: >Table Horizontal Rotation Angle
table_lines.comment: Rotation of the table in the horizontal plane (clockwise when looking from above the table).

table_lines.name: >Table Head Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment: Angle of the head-feet axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane. Positive values indicate that the head of the table is upwards.

table_lines.name: >Table Cradle Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment: Angle of the left-right axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane. Positive values indicate that the left of the table is upwards.

table_lines.name: Collimator Shape Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the collimator shape.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Collimator Shape
table_lines.comment:
Shape(s) of the collimator.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each Enumerated Value.

table_lines.name: >Vertices of the Polygonal Collimator
table_lines.comment:
Required if Collimator Shape (0018,1700) is POLYGONAL.
Multiple Values where the first set of two values are:
row of the origin vertex;
column of the origin vertex.
Two or more pairs of values follow and are the effective pixel row and column coordinates of the other vertices of the polygon collimator. Polygon collimators are implicitly closed from the last vertex to the origin vertex and all edges shall be non-intersecting except at the vertices. See

C.8.19.6-13.table_caption: X-Ray Isocenter Reference System Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Isocenter Reference System Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the Isocenter Reference Coordinate System (O, X, Y, Z).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Isocenter Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray center beam in the isocenter reference system in the X direction (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Positioner Isocenter Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray center beam in the isocenter reference system in the Z direction (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Positioner Isocenter Detector Rotation Angle
table_lines.comment:
Rotation of the X-Ray detector plane (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Table X Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
X position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Y Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Y position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Z Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Z position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Horizontal Rotation Angle
table_lines.comment:
Rotation of the table in the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: >Table Head Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the head-feet axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: >Table Cradle Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the left-right axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: X-Ray Geometry Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the geometric properties for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Isocenter
table_lines.comment: Distance from source to isocenter in mm.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment: Distance from source to receptor plane perpendicular to the receptor plane in mm.

table_lines.name: Preferred Playback Sequencing
table_lines.comment: Describes the preferred playback sequencing for a multi-frame image.

table_lines.name: Frame Display Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that specifies the display frame rate of a selected set of frames. The Items are ordered in increasing frame number. The range of the frames may not overlap and the ranges shall be adjacent.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Start Trim
table_lines.comment: The Frame Number of the first frame of the set of frames to be displayed in this Item.

table_lines.name: >Stop Trim
table_lines.comment: The Frame Number of the last frame of the set of frames to be displayed in this Item.

table_lines.name: >Skip Frame Range Flag
table_lines.comment: A flag indicating that the range of frames in this Item may be skipped.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display Frame Rate in Float
table_lines.comment: Recommended rate at which the frames of this Item should be displayed in frames/second.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Viewing Mode
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the recommended viewing protocol(s).
When this Attribute is present with a value, this value shall override the value of Recommended Viewing Mode (0028,1090) specified in the

table_lines.name: >Display Filter Percentage
table_lines.comment: Edge enhancement filter percentage that is recommended by the pixel data creator as filter presetting for display purposes. The value of 100 corresponds to the maximum filter strength that can be applied by a specific application displaying the image.

table_lines.name: >Mask Visibility Percentage
table_lines.comment: Required if Recommended Viewing Mode (0028,1090) equals SUB.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment: Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series

table_lines.name: Series Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this Series

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Image Type
table_lines.comment: Value 1 shall be DERIVED. Value 2 shall be PRIMARY. No other values shall be present.

table_lines.name: Total Pixel Matrix Columns
table_lines.comment: Required if Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Total Pixel Matrix Rows
table_lines.comment: Required if Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Total Pixel Matrix Focal Planes
table_lines.comment: Required if Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Total Pixel Matrix Origin Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Location of pixel 1\1 of the total pixel matrix in the Slide Coordinate System Frame of Reference.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >X Offset in Slide Coordinate System
table_lines.comment: The X offset in millimeters from the Origin of the Slide Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: >Y Offset in Slide Coordinate System
table_lines.comment: The Y offset in millimeters from the Origin of the Slide Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Image Orientation (Slide)
table_lines.comment: Required if Plane Position (Slide) Sequence (0048,021A) is present within a Functional Group Sequence or Dimension Organization Type (0020,9311) is present with a value of TILED_FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime), or is derived from lossy compressed images.
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if present in the source images or this IOD Instance has been compressed.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if present in the source images or this IOD Instance has been compressed. See

table_lines.name: Segmentation Type
table_lines.comment:
The type of encoding used to indicate the presence of the segmented property at a pixel/voxel location.
See

table_lines.name: Segmentation Fractional Type
table_lines.comment:
For fractional segmentation encoding, the meaning of the fractional value.
Required if Segmentation Type (0062,0001) is FRACTIONAL.
See

table_lines.name: Maximum Fractional Value
table_lines.comment: Specifies the value that represents a probability of 1 or complete occupancy. There shall be no values in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) greater than this value. Required if Segmentation Type (0062,0001) is FRACTIONAL.

table_lines.name: Segments Overlap
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not any segments in this Instance overlap. I.e., whether or not any pixel is or might be in more than one segment.
See

table_lines.name: Segment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the segments that are contained within the data.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Segment Algorithm Name
table_lines.comment: The name(s) of algorithm(s) used to generate the segment. Required if Segment Algorithm Type (0062,0008) is not MANUAL.

table_lines.name: >Segmentation Algorithm Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A description of how this segment was derived.
Algorithm Name (0066,0036) within this Sequence may be identical to Segment Algorithm Name (0062,0009).
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display Grayscale Value
table_lines.comment: A default single gray unsigned value in which it is recommended that the maximum pixel value in this segment be rendered on a monochrome display. The units are specified in P-Values from a minimum of 0000H (black) up to a maximum of FFFFH (white).

table_lines.name: Segment Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Segment Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the segment described in Segment Sequence (0062,0002) by reference to Segment Number (0062,0004). Referenced Segment Number (0062,000B) shall not be multi-valued.

table_lines.name: Segment Label
table_lines.comment: User-defined label identifying this segment. This may be the same as Code Meaning (0008,0104) of Segmented Property Type Code Sequence (0062,000F).

table_lines.name: Segment Description
table_lines.comment: User-defined description for this segment.

table_lines.name: Segment Algorithm Type
table_lines.comment: Type of algorithm used to generate the segment.

table_lines.usage:
May not be necessary if the anatomy is implicit in the Segmented Property Type Code Sequence.

More than one Item in Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) may be used when a region of interest spans multiple anatomical locations and there is not a single pre-coordinated code describing the combination of locations. There is no requirement that the multiple locations be contiguous.

table_lines.name: Segmented Property Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the general category of the property the segment represents.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Segmented Property Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the specific property the segment represents.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Property Type Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the modifier of the property type of this segment.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Tracking ID
table_lines.comment:
A text label used for tracking a finding or feature, potentially across multiple reporting objects, over time. This label shall be unique within the domain in which it is used.
Required if Tracking UID (0062,0021) is present.

table_lines.name: Tracking UID
table_lines.comment:
A unique identifier used for tracking a finding or feature, potentially across multiple reporting objects, over time.
Required if Tracking ID (0062,0020) is present.

table_lines.name: Definition Source Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instances containing the source of the Segment information.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced ROI Number
table_lines.comment:
The value of ROI Number (3006,0022) in the referenced SOP Instance that identifies the ROI that is the origin of the Segment information.
Required if Referenced SOP Class UID (0008,1150) is RT Structure Set Storage ("1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.481.3").

table_lines.name: Image Type
table_lines.comment:
Image identification characteristics.
See

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each voxel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits allocated.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each voxel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits stored.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit. Shall be one less than the value in Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples (color planes) in this image shall have a value of 1.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment: Specifies the intended interpretation of the voxel data.

table_lines.name: Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator
See

table_lines.name: Burned In Annotation
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the image was acquired.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Referenced Image Evidence Sequence
table_lines.comment:
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) is present.

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about the image.

table_lines.name: Quality Control Image
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not this image is a quality control or phantom image.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not be a quality control or phantom image.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the Image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment: Specifies a predefined identity transformation for the Presentation LUT such that the output of all grayscale transformations, if any, are defined to be in P-Values.

table_lines.name: Source Irradiation Event Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of Irradiation Events that were produced in this acquisition context.
See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Irradiation Event UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identification of the irradiation event(s) associated with the acquisition of this image.

C.8.21.2.1-1.table_caption: X-Ray 3D Angiographic Image Contributing Sources Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Contributing Sources Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes characteristics of the sources that are used to create a derived SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Device Processing Description
table_lines.comment:
Indicates any visual processing performed on the frame prior to exchange.
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Device Processing Code
table_lines.comment:
Code representing the device-specific processing associated with the frame (e.g., Organ Filtering code)
Required if present and have an equal value in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Plane Identification
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the plane used to acquire this image.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Imager Pixel Spacing
table_lines.comment:
Physical distance measured at the receptor plane of the detector between the centers of each pixel specified by a numeric pair - row spacing value (delimiter) column spacing value in mm.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

C.8.21.2.2-1.table_caption: X-Ray 3D Craniofacial Image Contributing Sources Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Contributing Sources Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes characteristics of the sources that are used to create a derived SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Device Processing Description
table_lines.comment:
Indicates any visual processing performed on the frame prior to exchange.
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Device Processing Code
table_lines.comment:
Code representing the device-specific processing associated with the frame (e.g., Organ Filtering code).
Required if present and have an equal value in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Imager Pixel Spacing
table_lines.comment:
Physical distance measured at the receptor plane of the detector between the centers of each pixel specified by a numeric pair - row spacing value (delimiter) column spacing value in mm.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

C.8.21.2.3-1.table_caption: Breast Tomosynthesis Contributing Sources Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Contributing Sources Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes characteristics of the sources that are used to create a derived SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Detector Type
table_lines.comment: The type of detector used to acquire this image.

table_lines.name: >Detector ID
table_lines.comment: The ID or serial number of the detector used to acquire this image.

table_lines.name: >Date of Last Detector Calibration
table_lines.comment: The date on which the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) was last calibrated.

table_lines.name: >Time of Last Detector Calibration
table_lines.comment: The time at which the detector used to acquire this image as identified in Detector ID (0018,700A) was last calibrated.

C.8.21.3.1.1-1.table_caption: X-Ray 3D General Shared Acquisition Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Source Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that identifies the set of Images that constitute this acquisition context.
Required if the reconstruction is created from DICOM SOP Instances.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Field of View Dimension(s) in Float
table_lines.comment:
Dimensions in mm of the Field of View in the source projection images. If Field of View Shape (0018,1147) is:
RECTANGLE: row dimension followed by column.
ROUND: diameter.
HEXAGONAL: diameter of the circle circumscribing the hexagon.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Field of View Origin
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the TLHC of a rectangle circumscribing the Field of View in the referenced images, before rotation or flipping, from the TLHC of the physical detector area measured in physical detector pixels as a row offset followed by a column offset.
See
Required if X-Ray Receptor Type (0018,9420) is present and equals DIGITAL_DETECTOR.

table_lines.name: Field of View Rotation
table_lines.comment:
Clockwise rotation in degrees of Field of View in the referenced images, relative to the physical detector.
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Field of View Horizontal Flip
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not a horizontal flip has been applied to the Field of View in the referenced images, after rotation relative to the physical detector as described in Field of View Rotation (0018,7032).
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Grid
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: KVP
table_lines.comment:
Average of the peak kilo voltage outputs of the X-Ray generator used for all frames.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment:
Average of the nominal X-Ray tube currents in milliamperes for all frames.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Exposure Time in ms
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment:
The total (cumulative) exposure for all frames expressed in milliampereseconds, for example calculated from Exposure Time and X-Ray Tube Current.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Contrast/Bolus Agent
table_lines.comment:
Contrast or bolus agent.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Contrast/Bolus Agent Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the contrast agent.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG and contrast media was applied.

table_lines.name: Start Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment:
Start date and time of that part of an acquisition used for this acquisition context.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: End Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment:
End date and time of that part of an acquisition used for this acquisition context.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

C.8.21.3.1.2-1.table_caption: X-Ray 3D General Per Projection Acquisition Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: KVP
table_lines.comment:
Exact peak kilo voltage output of the X-Ray generator used for this projection.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment:
Exact Nominal X-Ray tube current in milliamperes applied during the Frame Acquisition Duration (0018,9220) for this projection.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Frame Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Collimator Shape
table_lines.comment:
Shape(s) of the collimator.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each Enumerated Value.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

C.8.21.3.1.3-1.table_caption: X-Ray 3D General Positioner Movement Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Primary Positioner Scan Arc
table_lines.comment:
Total amount of rotation of the primary positioner in degrees.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Primary Positioner Scan Start Angle
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances. Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG.

table_lines.name: Primary Positioner Increment
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Primary Positioner Increment Sign
table_lines.comment:
Direction of the primary positioner rotation.
See
See

table_lines.name: Secondary Positioner Scan Arc
table_lines.comment:
Total amount of rotation of the secondary positioner in degrees.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Secondary Positioner Scan Start Angle
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Secondary Positioner Increment
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: Secondary Positioner Increment Sign
table_lines.comment:
Direction of the secondary positioner rotation.
See
See

table_lines.name: X-Ray 3D Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Each Item represents an acquisition context related to one or more reconstructions.
The values of Acquisition Index (0020,9518) may be used as index to Items in this Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Field of View Shape
table_lines.comment:
Shape of the Field of View in the referenced images.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Receptor Type
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the type of X-Ray receptor used.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Physical Detector Size
table_lines.comment:
Dimensions of the physical detector measured in mm as a row size followed by a column size.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Position of Isocenter Projection
table_lines.comment:
Position of the Isocenter measured in physical detector elements as a row offset followed by a column offset from the TLHC of a rectangle circumscribing the physical detector area.
Required if Isocenter Reference System Sequence (0018,9462) is present and if the values are present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Distance from source to isocenter in mm.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Focal Spot(s)
table_lines.comment:
Nominal focal spot size in mm used to acquire this image.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Type
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Material
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Thickness Minimum
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Thickness Maximum
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Beam Path Length Minimum
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Filter Beam Path Length Maximum
table_lines.comment: Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Table X Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
X position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Y Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Y position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Z Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Z position of the Table Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See

table_lines.name: >Table Horizontal Rotation Angle
table_lines.comment:
Rotation of the table in the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: >Table Head Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the head-feet axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: >Table Cradle Tilt Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the left-right axis of the table in degrees relative to the horizontal plane.
See

table_lines.name: >Per Projection Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing detailed acquisition context of each individual projection used in this acquisition context.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Isocenter Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray center beam for this projection in the isocenter reference system in the X direction (deg).
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Isocenter Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray center beam for this projection in the isocenter reference system in the Z direction (deg).
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Isocenter Detector Rotation Angle
table_lines.comment:
Rotation of the X-Ray detector plane for this projection (deg).
See
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray Image Intensifier about the patient from the RAO to LAO direction where movement from RAO to vertical is positive.
See

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position of the X-Ray Image Intensifier about the patient from the CAU to CRA direction where movement from CAU to vertical is positive.
See

table_lines.name: X-Ray 3D Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Each Item represents a acquisition context related to a set of frames of SOP Instance defined by this IOD,
The values of Acquisition Index (0020,9518) may be used as index to Items in this Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Field of View Shape
table_lines.comment:
Shape of the Field of View in the referenced images.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Receptor Type
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the type of X-Ray receptor used.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: >Per Projection Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing detailed acquisition context of each individual projection used in this acquisition context.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if present and consistent in the contributing SOP Instances.

table_lines.name: X-Ray 3D Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Each Item represents an acquisition context related to one or more reconstructions.
The values of Acquisition Index (0020,9518) may be used as index in this Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Field of View Shape
table_lines.comment: Shape of the Field of View in the source projection images.

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Receptor Type
table_lines.comment: Identifies the type of X-Ray receptor used.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm from source to detector center on the chest wall line.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Patient
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm from source to the breast support side that is closest to the Imaging Subject, as measured along the X-Ray beam vector.

table_lines.name: >Estimated Radiographic Magnification Factor
table_lines.comment: Ratio of Source Image Receptor Distance (SID) over Source Object Distance (SOD).

table_lines.name: >Anode Target Material
table_lines.comment: The primary material in the anode of the X-Ray source.

table_lines.name: >Body Part Thickness
table_lines.comment: The average thickness in mm of the body part examined when compressed, if compression has been applied during exposure.

table_lines.name: >Exposure Control Mode
table_lines.comment: Type of exposure control.

table_lines.name: >Exposure Control Mode Description
table_lines.comment:
Text description of the mechanism of exposure control.
May describe the number and type of exposure sensors or position of the sensitive area of the imaging detector.

table_lines.name: >Half Value Layer
table_lines.comment: The thickness of Aluminum in mm required to reduce the X-Ray Output (0040,0312) by a factor of two.

table_lines.name: >Organ Dose
table_lines.comment: Organ dose value measured in dGy representing the collective total for all acquired frames described in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: >Entrance Dose in mGy
table_lines.comment: Entrance dose value measured in mGy at the surface of the patient representing the collective total for all acquired frames described in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: >Entrance Dose Derivation
table_lines.comment:
Describes what type of dose is represented by the values of Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302).
Only meaningful if Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302) is present.

table_lines.name: >Focal Spot(s)
table_lines.comment: Nominal focal spot size in mm used to acquire the projection images.

table_lines.name: >Detector Binning
table_lines.comment:
Number of active detectors used to generate a single pixel. Specified as number of row detectors per pixel then column.
Required if detector binning was applied to the projection images.

table_lines.name: >Detector Temperature
table_lines.comment: Detector temperature during exposure in degrees Celsius.

table_lines.name: >Compression Force
table_lines.comment: The compression force applied to the body part during exposure, measured in Newtons.

table_lines.name: >Compression Pressure
table_lines.comment: The average compression pressure applied to the body part during exposure, calculated in kPa.

table_lines.name: >Compression Contact Area
table_lines.comment: The area of the body part to which compression has been applied during exposure, measured in mm2.

table_lines.name: >Paddle Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the compression paddle, if compression was applied to the body part during exposure.

table_lines.name: >Per Projection Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing detailed acquisition context of each individual projection used in this acquisition context.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Primary Angle
table_lines.comment: Signed position in degrees of the X-Ray beam vector in the coronal anatomical plane as if the patient were standing facing the equipment where vertical is zero.

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Primary Angle Direction
table_lines.comment:
The interpretation of the sign of the Positioner Primary Angle (0018,1510).
See

table_lines.name: >>Positioner Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position in degrees of the X-Ray beam vector in the sagittal anatomical plane as if the patient were standing where movement of the X-Ray source from anterior to posterior is positive, and vertical is zero.
Required if secondary positioner was used during acquisition.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment: The exposure expressed in milliampereseconds, for example calculated from Exposure Time and X-Ray Tube Current.

table_lines.name: >>Relative X-Ray Exposure
table_lines.comment: Indication of the applied dose, in manufacturer specific units.

table_lines.name: >>Organ Dose
table_lines.comment: Average organ dose value measured in dGy.

table_lines.name: >>Entrance Dose in mGy
table_lines.comment: Average entrance dose value measured in mGy at the surface of the patient during the acquisition of this projection image.

table_lines.name: >>Entrance Dose Derivation
table_lines.comment:
Describes what type of dose is represented by the values of Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302).
Only meaningful if Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Irradiation Event UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identification of the irradiation event(s) associated with the acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: X-Ray 3D Reconstruction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items each describing the characteristics of one 3D reconstruction included in this SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Description
table_lines.comment: Free text description of the purpose of the reconstruction, e.g., mask volume.

table_lines.name: >Application Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the application that created the reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Application Version
table_lines.comment: Version of the application that created the reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Application Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Name of the manufacturer of the application that created the reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Algorithm Type
table_lines.comment: Type of algorithm used to create the reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Algorithm Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the algorithm used to create the reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Index
table_lines.comment: The Item number(s) of the X-Ray 3D Acquisition Sequence (0018,9507) that describes the acquisition context(s) contributing to this reconstruction.

table_lines.name: X-Ray 3D Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes general characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008), except that the value MIXED is not allowed. See

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Index
table_lines.comment:
The Item number of the X-Ray 3D Reconstruction Sequence (0018,9530) that describes the characteristics of the 3D Reconstruction to which this frame is part of.
Required if the X-Ray 3D Reconstruction Sequence (0018,9530) is present.

table_lines.name: Biopsy Target Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the targets of a biopsy procedure. One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence for this frame, where the coordinate system is the same for all Items within a pair of stereo images.
Required if one or more biopsy targets are present for this frame.

table_lines.name: >Target UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier for the target.

table_lines.name: >Localizing Cursor Position
table_lines.comment: Coordinates of localizing cursor position with respect to pixels in the image specified by a column (delimiter) row pair. The values shall be in the range 0\0 (TLHC) to Columns\Rows (BRHC).

table_lines.name: >Calculated Target Position
table_lines.comment:
The calculated target position (x, y, z) in mm in an equipment relative right-handed coordinate system where the origin is under the central X-Ray beam at the chest wall, and a z value of zero is located at the surface that the breast is in contact with that is closest to the detector.
X is parallel to the chest wall, y is positive toward the patient's nipple, and z is positive toward the X-Ray source.

table_lines.name: >Displayed Z Value
table_lines.comment: The z value in mm displayed to the user at the time of biopsy.

table_lines.name: >Target Label
table_lines.comment: Target description.

table_lines.name: Image Type
table_lines.comment:
Image identification characteristics.
See

table_lines.name: View Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes the view of the patient anatomy in this image.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >View Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that provides modifiers for the view of the patient anatomy.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Breast Implant Present
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not the imaged breast contains a breast implant regardless of the visibility of a breast implant in the Pixel Data.
Required if Modality (0008,0060) is MG. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Partial View
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether this image is a partial view, that is a subset of a single view of the breast.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not be a partial view.
If this Attribute is present, its value shall be NO if there is a View Modifier Code Sequence (0054,0222) Item of value

table_lines.name: Partial View Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes the portion or section of the breast captured in a partial view image.
One or two Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Partial View (0028,1350) is present with a value of YES.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the images in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Related Series Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Required if another Series was used to perform attenuation correction and the SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Study Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Instance UID of Study to which the related Series belongs

table_lines.name: >Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Instance UID of Related Series

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
When absent, implies that the reason for the reference is unknown.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Start Condition
table_lines.comment:
Description of how the data collection was started.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Start Density Threshold
table_lines.comment: The count density that triggered the start of the acquisition, in counts/sec. Required if Acquisition Start Condition (0018,0073) equals DENS.

table_lines.name: Start Relative Density Difference Threshold
table_lines.comment: The relative count density that triggered the start of the acquisition, in counts/sec. Required if Acquisition Start Condition (0018,0073) equals RDD.

table_lines.name: Start Cardiac Trigger Count Threshold
table_lines.comment: The number of cardiac triggers that occurred before starting the acquisition. Required if Acquisition Start Condition (0018,0073) equals CARD_TRIG.

table_lines.name: Start Respiratory Trigger Count Threshold
table_lines.comment: The number of respiratory triggers that occurred before starting the acquisition. Required if Acquisition Start Condition (0018,0073) equals RESP_TRIG.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Termination Condition
table_lines.comment:
Description of how the data collection for the Series was stopped.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Termination Counts Threshold
table_lines.comment:
The count value that triggered the termination of the acquisition.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals CNTS.

table_lines.name: Termination Density Threshold
table_lines.comment:
The count density that triggered the termination of the acquisition, in counts/sec.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals DENS.

table_lines.name: Termination Relative Density Threshold
table_lines.comment:
The count relative density that triggered the termination of the acquisition, in counts/sec.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals RDD.

table_lines.name: Termination Time Threshold
table_lines.comment:
The time duration after which the acquisition was terminated, in sec.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals TIME

table_lines.name: Termination Cardiac Trigger Count Threshold
table_lines.comment:
