The number of cardiac triggers that triggered the termination of the acquisition.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals CARD_TRIG

table_lines.name: Termination Respiratory Trigger Count Threshold
table_lines.comment:
The number of respiratory triggers that triggered the termination of the acquisition.
Required if Acquisition Termination Condition (0018,0071) equals RESP_TRIG

table_lines.name: Type of Detector Motion
table_lines.comment:
Describes the type of detector motion during acquisition.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Detector Geometry
table_lines.comment:
Physical arrangement of the detectors in the acquisition system.
The radiation entrance surface of a detector may be curved or flat. A curved surface is referred to as cylindrical.
Detectors may simultaneously subtend all possible transverse angles from the center of the field of view. Detectors that do not are referred to as partial.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL and Type of Detector Motion (0054,0202) equals STATIONARY. May be present otherwise, if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED and Type of Detector Motion (0054,0202) equals STATIONARY.

table_lines.name: Transverse Detector Separation
table_lines.comment:
Distance between opposing detectors, in mm.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Axial Detector Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Axial detector size in mm. Size of the detector along the table axis.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Collimator Type
table_lines.comment:
Collimator Type.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Coincidence Window Width
table_lines.comment:
The width of the coincidence-timing window, in nanoseconds. The maximum time difference between two single events in two opposing detectors that will be accepted as a coincidence event.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Energy Window Range Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that describes the energy windows used for this Image.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Energy Window Lower Limit
table_lines.comment: The lower limit of the energy window, in KeV.

table_lines.name: >Energy Window Upper Limit
table_lines.comment: The upper limit of the energy window, in KeV.

table_lines.name: Time of Flight Information Used
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether or not Time-of-Flight information was used in creation of the image.

table_lines.name: Isocenter Position
table_lines.comment: Isocenter coordinates (x,y,z), in mm. Specifies the location of the machine isocenter in the Patient-Based Coordinate System associated with the Frame of Reference. It allows transformation from the Equipment-Based Coordinate System to the Patient-Based Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Scan Progression Direction
table_lines.comment: The anatomical order in which the slices were acquired.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Number
table_lines.comment: A number identifying the single continuous gathering of data over a period of time that resulted in this image, which may include multiple bed positions.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment:
The date and time that the acquisition of data started.
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL and SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples (planes) in this image. This value shall be 1.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the intended interpretation of the pixel data.
See

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits allocated. This value shall be 16.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits stored. This value shall be 16.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit. Shall be one less than the value in Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator
See

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about the image

table_lines.name: Burned in Annotation
table_lines.comment:
Indicates that the image does not contain burned in annotations.
This means that images that contain this Module shall not contain burned in annotations.
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted), may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See
Required if SOP Class UID is not "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment: Specifies an identity transformation for the Presentation LUT, such that the output of all grayscale transformations defined in the IOD containing this Module are defined to be P-Values.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the Image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Radiopharmaceutical Information Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that describe isotope information.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Agent Number
table_lines.comment: Identifying number, unique within this SOP Instance, of the agent administered. Used to reference this particular agent from the Radiopharmaceutical Functional Group Macro. The number shall be 1 for the first Item and increase by 1 for each subsequent Item.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the radionuclide.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Administration Route Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the administration route of the radiopharmaceutical.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Volume
table_lines.comment: Volume of administered radiopharmaceutical in cubic cm.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Start DateTime
table_lines.comment: Time of start of administration. The actual time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Stop DateTime
table_lines.comment: Time of end of administration. The actual ending time of radiopharmaceutical administration to the patient for imaging purposes.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Total Dose
table_lines.comment: The radiopharmaceutical dose administered to the patient measured in MegaBecquerels (MBq) at the Radiopharmaceutical Start DateTime (0018,1078).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Administration Event UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identification of the administration of the radiopharmaceutical to the patient.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Half Life
table_lines.comment: The radionuclide half life, in seconds, that was used in the correction of this image.

table_lines.name: >Radionuclide Positron Fraction
table_lines.comment: The radionuclide positron fraction (fraction of decays that are by positron emission) that was used in the correction of this image.

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Specific Activity
table_lines.comment: The activity per unit mass of the radiopharmaceutical, in Bq/micromole, at the Radiopharmaceutical Start DateTime (0018,1078).

table_lines.name: >Radiopharmaceutical Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the radiopharmaceutical.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: PET Frame Type Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes general characteristics of this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008) Attribute, except that the value MIXED is not allowed unless the SOP Class UID is "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.128.1" (Legacy Converted). See

table_lines.name: PET Frame Acquisition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the PET acquisition mode.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Height
table_lines.comment: The distance in mm from the top of the patient table to the data collection center. The distance is positive when the table is below the data collection center.

table_lines.name: >Gantry/Detector Tilt
table_lines.comment: Nominal angle of tilt in degrees of the scanning gantry. Not intended for mathematical computations. Zero degrees means the gantry is not tilted, negative degrees are when the top of the gantry is tilted away from where the table enters the gantry.

table_lines.name: >Gantry/Detector Slew
table_lines.comment: Nominal angle of slew in degrees of the gantry. Not intended for mathematical computations. Zero degrees means the gantry is no slewed. Positive slew is moving the gantry on the patient's left toward the patient's superior, when the patient is supine.

C.8.22-12.table_caption: PET Detector Motion Details Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: PET Detector Motion Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the details of the motion of the Detector.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Rotation Direction
table_lines.comment: Direction of rotation of the detector about the gantry, as viewed while facing the gantry where the table enters the gantry.

table_lines.name: >Revolution Time
table_lines.comment: The time in seconds of a complete revolution of the detector around the gantry orbit.

table_lines.name: PET Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes defining the PET geometry.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Position
table_lines.comment:
Relative longitudinal position of acquisition location of this frame in mm from an implementation specific reference point. Shall be relative to the same reference point for all frames in this SOP Instance, but may be different from the reference point in other SOP Instances. Positions as the table moves into the gantry viewed from the front are more negative.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Data Collection Center (Patient)
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Target Center (Patient)
table_lines.comment: Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

C.8.22-15.table_caption: PET Frame Correction Factors Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: PET Frame Correction Factors Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes that describe the correction factors applied to this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Primary (Prompts) Counts Accumulated
table_lines.comment:
The sum of events that occur in the primary event channel. The counts include Trues +Scatter+ Randoms if Corrected Image (0028,0051) includes RAN; otherwise the counts are Trues +Scatter.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Slice Sensitivity Factor
table_lines.comment:
The slice-to-slice sensitivity correction factor that was used to correct this frame. The value shall be one if no slice sensitivity correction was applied.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Decay Factor
table_lines.comment:
The decay factor that was used to scale this frame.
Required if Decay Corrected (0018,9758) equals YES.

table_lines.name: >Scatter Fraction Factor
table_lines.comment:
An estimate of the fraction of acquired counts that were due to scatter and that were corrected in this frame. The value shall be zero if no scatter correction was applied.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Dead Time Factor
table_lines.comment:
The average dead time correction factor that was applied to this frame. The value shall be one if no dead time correction was applied.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: PET Reconstruction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes describing the reconstruction process for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Type
table_lines.comment:
Description of the type of algorithm used when reconstructing the image from the data acquired during the acquisition process.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Algorithm
table_lines.comment:
Description of the algorithm used when reconstructing the image from the data acquired during the acquisition process.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 of this frame is ORIGINAL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Iterative Reconstruction Method
table_lines.comment: Iterative Reconstruction Method used.

table_lines.name: >Number of Iterations
table_lines.comment:
Number of iterations.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL and Iterative Reconstruction Method (0018,9769) equals YES. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Number of Subsets
table_lines.comment:
Number of subsets.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL and Iterative Reconstruction Method (0018,9769) equals YES. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Diameter
table_lines.comment:
The diameter defines a circular region that is entirely contained within the encoded Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), unless the encoded image has been cropped after reconstruction.
Required if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL and Reconstruction Field of View (0018,9317) is not present.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals DERIVED and Reconstruction Field of View (0018,9317) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Field of View
table_lines.comment:
The field of view width followed by height as used for reconstruction in mm.
Required if Image Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals ORIGINAL and Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) is not present.
Otherwise may be present if Frame Type (0008,9007) Value 1 equals DERIVED and Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) is not present.

table_lines.name: PET Table Dynamics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Attributes describing the movement of the PET Table.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Table Speed
table_lines.comment: The distance in mm that the Table moves in one second during the gathering of data that resulted in this frame.

table_lines.name: Counts Source
table_lines.comment: The primary source of counts.

table_lines.name: Decay Corrected
table_lines.comment: Decay (DECY) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Attenuation Corrected
table_lines.comment: Attenuation (ATTN) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Scatter Corrected
table_lines.comment: Scatter (SCAT) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Dead Time Corrected
table_lines.comment: Dead time (DTIM) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Gantry Motion Corrected
table_lines.comment: Gantry motion (MOTN) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Patient Motion Corrected
table_lines.comment: Patient motion (PMOT) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Count Loss Normalization Corrected
table_lines.comment: Count loss (CLN) normalization correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Randoms Corrected
table_lines.comment: Randoms (RAN) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Non-uniform Radial Sampling Corrected
table_lines.comment: Non-uniform radial sampling (RADL) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Sensitivity Calibrated
table_lines.comment: Image is sensitivity calibrated using a dose calibrator (DCAL).

table_lines.name: Detector Normalization Correction
table_lines.comment: Detector normalization (NORM) correction has been applied to image.

table_lines.name: Randoms Correction Method
table_lines.comment:
Type of randoms correction processing.
Required if Randoms Corrected (0018,9765) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Attenuation Correction Source
table_lines.comment: Required if Attenuation Corrected (0018,9759) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Attenuation Correction Temporal Relationship
table_lines.comment: Required if Attenuation Corrected (0018,9759) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Scatter Correction Method
table_lines.comment:
A textual description of the scatter correction processing. e.g., convolution-subtraction, dual energy window, model-based, use of attenuation data.
Required if Scatter Corrected (0018,9760) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Decay Correction DateTime
table_lines.comment:
The date and time to which all frames in this Image were decay corrected.
Required if Decay Corrected (0018,9758) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Segment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the segments that are contained within the data.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Surface Count
table_lines.comment: The number of surfaces that comprise this segment. Shall be greater than zero.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Surface Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence referencing the surfaces composed to construct this segment.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The number of Items shall equal the value of Surface Count (0066,002A).

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Surface Number
table_lines.comment: Identifies the Surface Number (0066,0003) within the Surface Sequence (0066,0002) to which this reference applies.

table_lines.name: >>Segment Surface Generation Algorithm Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A description of how this segment surface was derived.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: For Algorithm Family Code Sequence (0066,002F) B

table_lines.name: >>Segment Surface Source Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that identifies the set of Instances by their SOP Class/Instance pair that were used to derive this segment surface.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the images in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Performed Protocol Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence describing a Protocol being followed for this Procedure Step.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Protocol is controlling the creation of this Series. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Protocol Context Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that specifies the context for the Performed Protocol Code Sequence (0040,0260) Item.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Content Item Modifier Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that specifies modifiers for a Protocol Context Content Item.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: Performed Protocol Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of protocol performed.
Required if Performed Protocol Code Sequence (0040,0260) is present.

C.8.24.2-1.table_caption: Ultrasound Frame of Reference Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Volume Frame of Reference UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies this Volume Frame of Reference.

table_lines.name: Ultrasound Acquisition Geometry
table_lines.comment: Characteristic of the ultrasound acquisition geometry.

table_lines.name: Apex Position
table_lines.comment:
Position of the apex (or phase center) of the acquisition geometry, encoded as x
Required if value of Ultrasound Acquisition Geometry (0020,9307) is APEX.

table_lines.name: Volume to Transducer Relationship
table_lines.comment:
Relationship between the transducer and the acquired volume.
Required if the transducer position and/or orientation relative to the volume is not constant. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Patient Frame of Reference Source
table_lines.comment:
Indicates how the supplied Image Position (Patient) (0020,0032) and Image Orientation (Patient) (0020,0037) values are obtained.
Required if either Image Position (Patient) (0020,0032) or Image Orientation (Patient) (0020,0037) is present.

table_lines.name: Table Frame of Reference UID
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies this Table Frame of Reference.
Required if Patient Frame of Reference Source (0020,930C) is TABLE.

table_lines.name: Volume to Table Mapping Matrix
table_lines.comment: Required if Patient Frame of Reference Source (0020,930C) is TABLE.

table_lines.name: Image Type
table_lines.comment:
Image identification characteristics.
See

table_lines.name: Samples Per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples per pixel in this image.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment: Specifies the intended interpretation of the pixel data.

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample. Shall be equal to Bits Allocated (0028,0100).

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment: Most significant bit for pixel sample data. High Bit (0028,0102) shall be one less than Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Pixel Representation
table_lines.comment:
Data representation of pixel samples. The constrained Enumerated Value implies the VR of all Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptors be US (and not SS).
See

table_lines.name: Dimension Organization Type
table_lines.comment:
Dimension organization of the Instance.
See

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time that the acquisition of data that resulted in this image started.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: Duration of the image acquisition in seconds.

table_lines.name: Position Measuring Device Used
table_lines.comment:
Describes the type of position measuring device used in the acquisition of the image, if any. This gives an indication of the degree of precision of Pixel Spacing (0028,0030) and the spacing between adjacent planes.
Required if Volumetric Properties (0008,9206) is VOLUME and Volume Based Calculation Technique (0008,9207) is NONE. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment: Specifies an identity transformation for the Presentation LUT, such that the output of all grayscale transformations defined in the IOD containing this Module are defined to be P-Values.

table_lines.name: Rescale Intercept
table_lines.comment:
The value b in relationship between stored values (SV) and the output units.
Output units = m*SV + b.

table_lines.name: Rescale Slope
table_lines.comment: m in the equation specified by Rescale Intercept (0028,1052).

table_lines.name: Source Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that identifies the set of Image SOP Class/Instance pairs of the Images that were used to derive this Image.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Image Type (0008,0008) Value 1 is DERIVED.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that references other images significantly related to this image. (e.g., an image containing spatially related frames)
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Referenced Raw Data Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that identifies the set of Raw Data SOP Class/Instance pairs of the raw data that were used to derive this Image.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides reference to a set of non-image SOP Class/Instance pairs significantly related to this Image, including waveforms that may or may not be temporally synchronized with this image.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if waveforms are acquired in conjunction with image acquisition. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Code describing the purpose of the reference to the Instance(s).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Number of Stages
table_lines.comment:
Number of stages in this protocol.
Required if Performed Protocol Type (0040,0261) is present with value STAGED.

table_lines.name: Stage Number
table_lines.comment:
A number that identifies the Stage. Stage Number starts at one.
Required if Performed Protocol Type (0040,0261) is present with value STAGED.

table_lines.name: Stage Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence describing the performed Ultrasound Protocol Stage.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Performed Protocol Type (0040,0261) is present with value STAGED.

table_lines.name: Event Timer Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of time intervals of significance to this image. Each Item describes one time interval either beginning or ending at Acquisition DateTime (0008,002A).
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Event Time Offset
table_lines.comment: Signed value of the time between Acquisition DateTime (0008,002A) and the event, in milliseconds. Positive values indicate the event occurs after Acquisition DateTime (0008,002A).

table_lines.name: >Event Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Type of event.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Event Timer Name(s)
table_lines.comment:
Name that identifies the event timer. May be used in addition to Event Time Code Sequence to offer site-specific user-readable event time names.
Only a single value shall be included.

table_lines.name: Burned In Annotation
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not image contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the image was acquired.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the image or a reconstruction from a set of images to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the image may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Transducer Data
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer defined code or description

table_lines.name: Transducer Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the ultrasound transducer used.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Transducer Scan Pattern Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The scan pattern the transducer is capable of.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: Transducer Geometry Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Geometric structure of the transducer.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: Transducer Beam Steering Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Technique used by the transducer for beam steering.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
If more than one Item is present, the order is significant from plane-forming technique to volume-forming technique.
See

table_lines.name: Transducer Application Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The primary clinical application of the transducer.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: Processing Function
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer defined description of processing of echo information. Data may include code or description of gain (initial, overall, TGC, dynamic range, etc.), pre-processing, post-processing, Doppler processing parameters, e.g., cutoff filters, etc., as used in generating a given image.

table_lines.name: Depth(s) of Focus
table_lines.comment: The depth or depths from the transducer face, of the manufacturer defined beam focus points used for the image, in mm.

table_lines.name: Depth of Scan Field
table_lines.comment: The depth, in mm, from the transducer face to the deepest point included in the image- the field of view.

table_lines.name: IVUS Pullback Rate
table_lines.comment:
Required if IVUS Acquisition (0018,3100) value is MOTOR_PULLBACK. Specified in units of mm/sec.
See

table_lines.name: IVUS Gated Rate
table_lines.comment:
Required if IVUS Acquisition (0018,3100) value is GATED_PULLBACK. Specified in units of mm/beat.
See

table_lines.name: IVUS Pullback Start Frame Number
table_lines.comment:
Required if IVUS Acquisition (0018,3100) value is MOTOR_PULLBACK or GATED_PULLBACK.
See

table_lines.name: IVUS Pullback Stop Frame Number
table_lines.comment:
Required if IVUS Acquisition (0018,3100) value is MOTOR_PULLBACK or GATED_PULLBACK.
See

table_lines.name: Excluded Intervals Sequence
table_lines.comment:
List of excluded intervals.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if one or more intervals was excluded.

table_lines.name: >Exclusion Start DateTime
table_lines.comment: Time-point of the exclusion start in the same Synchronization Frame of Reference as Acquisition DateTime (0008,002A).

table_lines.name: >Exclusion Duration
table_lines.comment: Duration of the exclusion in ms.

table_lines.name: US Image Description Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes a general description of this image or frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame. A multi-valued Attribute analogous to Image Type (0008,0008).
Enumerated Values and Defined Terms are the same as those for the four values of Image Type (0008,0008), except that the value MIXED is not allowed. See

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Properties
table_lines.comment:
Indication if geometric manipulations are possible with frames in the SOP Instance.
See

table_lines.name: >Volume Based Calculation Technique
table_lines.comment:
Method used for volume calculations with frames in the SOP Instance.
See

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the measurements in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the measurements in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the measurements in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

C.8.25.4-1.table_caption: Subjective Refraction Measurements Series Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the measurements in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

C.8.25.5-1.table_caption: Visual Acuity Measurements Series Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that originally acquired the data used to create the measurements in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance to which the Series is related.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a Performed Procedure Step SOP Class was involved in the creation of this Series.

table_lines.name: Cylinder Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies lens measurements to correct for astigmatism or measurements of an eye that has astigmatism.
Required if astigmatic correction or astigmatism is measured.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Cylinder Power
table_lines.comment: The power that is present at the power meridian (90 degrees from the axis), in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Cylinder Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian, defined in degrees, that is 90 degrees from the power meridian.

table_lines.name: Prism Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies prism that is measured in a lens, or that is required to correct for a patient's ocular misalignment.
Required if prism is measured in the lens or if this part of a refraction is done for a patient.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Horizontal Prism Power
table_lines.comment: The power of a prism to bend light in the horizontal direction, in prism diopters.

table_lines.name: >Horizontal Prism Base
table_lines.comment: Direction of the base of the measured prism -- either in (toward the nose), or out (away from the nose)

table_lines.name: >Vertical Prism Power
table_lines.comment: The power of a prism to bend light in the vertical direction, in prism diopters.

table_lines.name: >Vertical Prism Base
table_lines.comment: Direction of the base of the measured prism -- either up, or down.

C.8.25.7-1.table_caption: General Ophthalmic Refractive Measurements Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies these measurements.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the measurements data creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the measurements data creation started.

table_lines.name: Measurement Laterality
table_lines.comment: Laterality of refractive measurement performed.

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about this SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Referenced Refractive Measurements Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies Ophthalmic Refractive Measurements SOP Instances that are relevant to the interpretation of this SOP Instance.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Visual Acuity Type Code Sequence (0046,0121) is present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Lens Description
table_lines.comment: A free text description of the lens and lens general comments.

table_lines.name: Right Lens Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies measurements of a patient's right lens.
Required if the right lens is measured.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Left Lens Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies measurements of a patient's left lens.
Required if the left lens is measured.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Unspecified Laterality Lens Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies measurements of one lens of unknown laterality.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Shall not be included if Attribute Right Lens Sequence (0046,0014) or Left Lens Sequence (0046,0015) is present.
Required if a single lens of unknown laterality is measured.

table_lines.name: Sphere Power
table_lines.comment: Refractive power of the lens that is the same in all meridians, measured at distance (optical infinity), in diopters.

table_lines.name: Add Near Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of the lens to correct for inability to focus at near while wearing the distance prescription.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Add Near is measured in the lens.

table_lines.name: >Add Power
table_lines.comment: Additional power relative to the distance correction, expressed in diopters, that allows best corrected visual acuity at the defined viewing distance.

table_lines.name: >Viewing Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance, in cm, for testing visual acuity corresponding to the value of Add Power (0046,0104) in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Add Intermediate Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of the lens to correct for inability to focus at intermediate distance while wearing the distance prescription.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Add intermediate is measured in the lens.

table_lines.name: >Add Power
table_lines.comment: Additional power relative to the distance correction, expressed in diopters, that allows best corrected visual acuity at the defined viewing distance.

table_lines.name: >Viewing Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance, in cm, for testing visual acuity corresponding to the value of Add Power (0046,0104) in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Lens Segment Type
table_lines.comment: The type of segment of a lens containing the "add" power, as described above

table_lines.name: Optical Transmittance
table_lines.comment: The fraction of light that passes through the measured lens optical media, in percent.

table_lines.name: Channel Width
table_lines.comment: In a progressive lens, the width in mm of that portion of the lens where there is gradual or progressive increase in "add" power.

table_lines.name: Autorefraction Right Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of a patient's right eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the right eye is measured.

table_lines.name: >Sphere Power
table_lines.comment: Refractive power of the eye that is the same in all meridians, measured at distance (optical infinity), in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Pupil Size
table_lines.comment: The horizontal diameter measurement of the pupil, in mm.

table_lines.name: >Corneal Size
table_lines.comment: The horizontal diameter measurement of the cornea, in mm.

table_lines.name: Autorefraction Left Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of a patient's left eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the left eye is measured.

table_lines.name: >Sphere Power
table_lines.comment: Refractive power of the eye that is the same in all meridians, measured at distance (optical infinity), in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Pupil Size
table_lines.comment: The horizontal diameter measurement of the pupil, in mm.

table_lines.name: >Corneal Size
table_lines.comment: The horizontal diameter measurement of the cornea, in mm.

table_lines.name: Distance Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is in the distance, as measured by an autorefractor.

table_lines.name: Near Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is at near, as measured by an autorefractor.

table_lines.name: Keratometry Right Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies keratometric measurements of a patient's right eye, defining principal meridians wherein the steepest meridian is separated by 90 degrees from the flattest.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the right eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Keratometry Left Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies keratometric measurements of a patient's left eye, defining principal meridians wherein the steepest meridian is separated by 90 degrees from the flattest.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the left eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Steep Keratometric Axis Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the steepest meridian as defined by the greatest power of curvature and shortest radius of curvature.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radius of Curvature
table_lines.comment: The radius of curvature of the principal meridians of the cornea, measured in mm.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridians, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian where the keratometric radius of curvature or power is measured, in degrees.

table_lines.name: Flat Keratometric Axis Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the flattest meridian as defined by the least power of curvature and longest radius of curvature.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radius of Curvature
table_lines.comment: The radius of curvature of the principal meridians of the cornea, measured in mm.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridians, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian where the keratometric radius of curvature or power is measured, in degrees.

table_lines.name: Subjective Refraction Right Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the subjective refractive measurements of a patient's right eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the right eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Subjective Refraction Left Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the subjective refractive measurements of a patient's left eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the left eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Distance Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is in the distance, as measured by a phoropter.

table_lines.name: Near Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is at near, as measured by a phoropter.

table_lines.name: Intermediate Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is at an intermediate distance, as measured by a phoropter.

table_lines.name: Other Pupillary Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm between the pupils when the patient's object of regard is at the distance specified in the Attribute Add Other Sequence (0046,0102), as measured by a phoropter.

table_lines.name: Sphere Power
table_lines.comment: Refractive power of the eye that is the same in all meridians, measured at distance (optical infinity), in diopters.

table_lines.name: Add Near Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of the eye to correct for inability to focus at near while wearing the distance prescription.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if near point refraction is done.

table_lines.name: >Add Power
table_lines.comment: Additional power relative to the distance correction, expressed in diopters, that allows best corrected visual acuity at the defined viewing distance.

table_lines.name: >Viewing Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance, in cm, for testing visual acuity corresponding to the value of Add Power (0046,0104) in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Add Intermediate Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of the eye to correct for inability to focus at intermediate distance while wearing the distance prescription.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if intermediate point refraction is done.

table_lines.name: >Add Power
table_lines.comment: Additional power relative to the distance correction, expressed in diopters, that allows best corrected visual acuity at the defined viewing distance.

table_lines.name: >Viewing Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance, in cm, for testing visual acuity using the value of Add Power (0046,0104) in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Add Other Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies refractive measurements of the eye to correct for inability to focus at the below specified distance while wearing the distance prescription.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if refraction is done at less than distance (optical infinity), but at a distance other than "near" or "intermediate".

table_lines.name: >Add Power
table_lines.comment: Additional power relative to the distance correction, expressed in diopters, that allows best corrected visual acuity at the defined viewing distance.

table_lines.name: >Viewing Distance
table_lines.comment: The distance, in cm, for testing visual acuity corresponding to the value of Add Power (0046,0104) in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Viewing Distance Type
table_lines.comment: The viewing distance conditions under which a patient's vision was measured.

table_lines.name: Visual Acuity Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the conditions under which a patient's vision was measured.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Background Color
table_lines.comment: The color of the background upon which optotypes are displayed for measurements of visual acuity.

table_lines.name: Optotype
table_lines.comment: The standardized test type (standard object of regard) used in measurements of visual acuity.

table_lines.name: Optotype Detailed Definition
table_lines.comment: Required if the Optotype (0046,0094) Attribute value is LETTERS or NUMBERS or PICTURES. Provides additional information to define what optotype was used.

table_lines.name: Optotype Presentation
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether single or multiple optotypes were presented.

table_lines.name: Visual Acuity Right Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the subjective measurement of a patient's visual acuity for the right eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the right eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Visual Acuity Left Eye Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the subjective measurements of a patient's visual acuity for the left eye.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the left eye is measured.

table_lines.name: Visual Acuity Both Eyes Open Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies a patient's subjective visual acuity measurements with both eyes open.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Decimal Visual Acuity
table_lines.comment: A patient's visual acuity specified in decimal. The value is derived from two values in a fraction where the numerator of the fraction is the nominal distance to the chart that the patient is reading. The denominator represents the line of smallest optotypes of which the patient can see more than half.

table_lines.name: Visual Acuity Modifiers
table_lines.comment:
The first value is a positive or negative integer numeric value such as +1, +2, +3, 0, -1, -2, or -3 used to indicate that the patient missed letters on the line referenced, or saw additional letters on the next smaller line.
The second value is a positive or negative integer numeric value such as +1, +2, +3, 0, -1, -2, or -3, which in combination with the first value indicates that the patient both saw additional letters on the next smaller line and missed letters on the line referenced.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridians, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis

table_lines.name: Flat Keratometric Axis Sequence

table_lines.name: >Radius of Curvature

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian where the keratometric radius of curvature or power is measured, in degrees.

table_lines.comment:
Descriptors relevant to keratometry data.

table_lines.name: Keratometer Index
table_lines.comment: The translation factor specific to each keratometer that derives a number for power from the measured radius of curvature of the cornea.

table_lines.name: >Ophthalmic Axial Length
table_lines.comment: The axial length of a patient's eye, in mm, that was used in calculation of IOL power.

table_lines.name: >Ophthalmic Axial Length Selection Method Code Sequence

table_lines.comment:
Method used for obtaining axial measurements of the eye.

table_lines.name: IOL Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Name of the manufacturer that produced the lens.

table_lines.name: Implant Name
table_lines.comment: The (product) name of the lens.

table_lines.name: Type of Optical Correction
table_lines.comment: Type of the optical correction achieved by the IOL.

table_lines.name: Lens Constant Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Constants used in calculation of intraocular lens power. These constants are a characteristic of the model of intraocular lens being considered for use in cataract surgery.

table_lines.name: >Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Constant type used in calculation of intraocular lens power.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Numeric Value
table_lines.comment: The value of the constant used.

table_lines.name: IOL Power Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information needed to select the intraocular lens power for cataract surgery.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >IOL Power
table_lines.comment:
The intraocular lens power, in diopters.
If Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC, this value represents the spherical equivalent of the toric intraocular lens power.

table_lines.name: >Toric IOL Power Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The toric intraocular lens power.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC.

table_lines.name: >Predicted Refractive Error
table_lines.comment: The predicted postoperative refractive error (i.e., amount of near or far sightedness), in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Predicted Toric Error Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The predicted postoperative toric error.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC.

table_lines.name: >Implant Part Number
table_lines.comment: The (product) identifier of the lens.

table_lines.name: >Pre-Selected for Implantation
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether the intraocular lens specified by this Sequence Item has been pre-selected for implantation or not.
Only one Item in IOL Power Sequence (0022,1090) shall contain the value YES.

table_lines.name: IOL Power for Exact Emmetropia
table_lines.comment:
The IOL power that would be required to achieve exact emmetropia, or no need for glasses at distance after surgery, in diopters.
If Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC, this value represents the spherical equivalent of the toric intraocular lens power for exact emmetropia.

table_lines.name: Toric IOL Power for Exact Emmetropia Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The toric IOL power that would be required to achieve exact emmetropia.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC.

table_lines.name: IOL Power for Exact Target Refraction
table_lines.comment:
The IOL power that would be required to exactly achieve Target Refraction (0022,1037), in diopters.
If Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC, this value represents the spherical equivalent of the toric intraocular lens power for exact target refraction.

table_lines.name: Toric IOL Power for Exact Target Refraction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The toric IOL power that would be required to exactly achieve Target Refraction (0022,1037).
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Type of Optical Correction (0022,1046) is TORIC.

table_lines.name: Calculation Comment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Comment, hints or warnings related to the intraocular lens calculation(s).
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Calculation Comment Type
table_lines.comment: The type of the Calculation Comment (0022,112C).

table_lines.name: >Calculation Comment
table_lines.comment: Comment related to the intraocular lens calculation(s).

table_lines.name: >Corneal Axis

table_lines.comment:
Flattest meridian as defined by the least power of curvature and longest radius of curvature.

table_lines.name: >Radius of Curvature
table_lines.comment: The radius of curvature of the principal meridians of the cornea, measured in mm.

table_lines.name: >Corneal Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridians, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Corneal Axis

Method of the cornea measurement.

C.8.26.2-1.table_caption: Visual Field Static Perimetry Test Parameters Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Visual Field Horizontal Extent
table_lines.comment: The maximum horizontal angular subtend (diameter or width) of the tested visual field, in degrees.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Vertical Extent
table_lines.comment: The maximum vertical angular subtend (diameter or height) of the tested visual field, in degrees.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Shape
table_lines.comment: The shape of the visual field tested.

table_lines.name: Screening Test Mode Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Mode used to determine how the starting luminance values and expected thresholds are chosen.

table_lines.name: Maximum Stimulus Luminance
table_lines.comment: Maximum luminance of stimulus, in candelas per square meter (cd/m²).

table_lines.name: Background Luminance
table_lines.comment: Background luminance of the device, in candelas per square meter (cd/m²).

table_lines.name: Stimulus Color Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Color of light stimulus presented to the patient.

table_lines.name: Background Illumination Color Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Color of the background illumination of the visual field device.

table_lines.name: Stimulus Area
table_lines.comment: Area of light stimulus presented to the patient, in degrees squared.

table_lines.name: Stimulus Presentation Time
table_lines.comment: The duration of time that a light stimulus is presented to a patient per each individual test point, in milliseconds.

C.8.26.3-1.table_caption: Visual Field Static Perimetry Test Reliability Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Fixation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The patient's gaze stability information during the visual field test.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Fixation Monitoring Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The device strategy used to monitor the patient's fixation.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Fixation Checked Quantity
table_lines.comment:
The number of times that the patient's gaze fixation is checked.
Required if Fixation Monitoring Code Sequence (0024,0033) contains an Item with the value

table_lines.name: >Patient Not Properly Fixated Quantity
table_lines.comment:
The number of times the patient's gaze is not properly fixated.
Required if Fixation Monitoring Code Sequence (0024,0033) contains an Item with the value

table_lines.name: >Excessive Fixation Losses Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to determine excessive fixation losses.

table_lines.name: >Excessive Fixation Losses
table_lines.comment:
The number of fixation losses is outside of implementation-specific limits.
Required if Excessive Fixation Losses Data Flag (0024,0039) is YES.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Catch Trial Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The reliability of the patient's responses to the visual field test.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Catch Trials Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether catch trials data were performed.

table_lines.name: >Negative Catch Trials Quantity
table_lines.comment:
Total number of times the patient's visual attention was tested using stimuli brighter than previously seen luminance (negative catch trials).
Required if Catch Trials Data Flag (0024,0055) is YES.

table_lines.name: >False Negatives Quantity
table_lines.comment:
Total number of stimuli that were not seen by the patient but were previously seen at a lower luminance earlier in the visual field test (false negatives).
Required if Catch Trials Data Flag (0024,0055) is YES.

table_lines.name: >False Negatives Estimate Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to estimates false negatives.

table_lines.name: >False Negatives Estimate
table_lines.comment:
Estimated percentage of all stimuli that were not seen by the patient but were previously seen at a lower luminance earlier in the visual field test (false negative responses), as percent.
Required if False Negatives Estimate Flag (0024,0045) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Excessive False Negatives Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to determine excessive false negatives.

table_lines.name: >Excessive False Negatives
table_lines.comment:
The false negative estimate is outside of implementation-specific limits.
Required if Excessive False Negatives Data Flag (0024,0051) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Positive Catch Trials Quantity
table_lines.comment:
The total number of times the device behaved as if it was going to present a visual stimulus but did not actually present the stimulus (positive catch trials).
Required if Catch Trials Data Flag (0024,0055) is YES.

table_lines.name: >False Positives Quantity
table_lines.comment:
The total number of patient responses that occurred at a time when no visual stimulus was present (false positive responses).
Required if Catch Trials Data Flag (0024,0055) is YES.

table_lines.name: >False Positives Estimate Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to estimate false positives.

table_lines.name: >False Positives Estimate
table_lines.comment:
Estimated percentage of all patient responses that occurred at a time when no visual stimulus was present (false positive responses), as percent.
Required if False Positives Estimate Flag (0024,0053) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Excessive False Positives Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to determine excessive false positives.

table_lines.name: >Excessive False Positives
table_lines.comment:
The false positive estimate is outside of implementation-specific limit.
Required if Excessive False Positives Data Flag (0024,0061) is YES.

table_lines.name: Stimuli Retesting Quantity
table_lines.comment: Total number of times in the course of a visual field exam that any location had to be retested at the same magnitude.

table_lines.name: Patient Reliability Indicator
table_lines.comment: Vendor implementation specific text to provide an analysis and/or summary of patient reliability indicator/indices.

table_lines.name: Comments on Patient's Performance of Visual Field
table_lines.comment: Operator's (test administrator) subjective comment on patient's performance.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Test Reliability Global Index Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information about various visual field indices related to test reliability.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

C.8.26.3-2.table_caption: Ophthalmic Visual Field Global Index Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Data Observation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information about various visual field global indexes.

Value Type (0040,A040) shall be NUMERIC or CODE.

Concept Name Code Sequence (0040,A043) D

Concept Code Sequence (0040,A168) D

table_lines.name: Index Normals Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether normative data exists for this index.

table_lines.name: Index Probability Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Probability value and software algorithm used to provide the index.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Index Normals Flag (0024,0338) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Index Probability
table_lines.comment: Probability for the index value within the normal population, in percent.

C.8.26.4-1.table_caption: Visual Field Static Perimetry Test Measurements Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Measurement Laterality
table_lines.comment:
Laterality of body part (eye) examined.
See

table_lines.name: Presented Visual Stimuli Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the device was able to determine presented visual stimuli.

table_lines.name: Number of Visual Stimuli
table_lines.comment:
The total number of visual stimuli presented to the patient. This includes the number of stimuli repetitions.
Required if Presented Visual Stimuli Data Flag (0024,0037) is YES.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Test Duration
table_lines.comment: Total time the visual field machine was actively presenting visual stimuli to patient, in seconds.

table_lines.name: Foveal Sensitivity Measured
table_lines.comment: Whether foveal sensitivity was measured.

table_lines.name: Foveal Sensitivity
table_lines.comment:
Foveal Sensitivity is the reciprocal of foveal threshold (1/foveal threshold), in dB.
Foveal Threshold is the minimum amount of luminance increment on a uniform background that can be detected by the patient at coordinates 0,0 (relative to the center of the patient's fixation).
See
Required if the value for Foveal Sensitivity Measured (0024,0086) is YES.

table_lines.name: Foveal Point Normative Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Existence of normative data base for the foveal point sensitivity.

table_lines.name: Foveal Point Probability Value
table_lines.comment:
The percentile of the foveal point sensitivity within an age corrected normal visual field, in percent.
Required if the value for Foveal Sensitivity Measured (0024,0086) is YES and Foveal Point Normative Data Flag (0024,0117) is YES.

table_lines.name: Screening Baseline Measured
table_lines.comment: Whether visual field screening baseline was measured.

table_lines.name: Screening Baseline Measured Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information about the starting luminance screening values.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the value for Screening Baseline Measured (0024,0120) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Screening Baseline Type
table_lines.comment: Method used to determine starting luminance screening values.

table_lines.name: >Screening Baseline Value
table_lines.comment: Visual Field screening baseline value, in dB.

table_lines.name: Blind Spot Localized
table_lines.comment: Whether the blind spot was measured.

table_lines.name: Blind Spot X-Coordinate
table_lines.comment:
The horizontal coordinate of the patient's blind spot relative to the center of the patient's fixation, in degrees, such that toward the right is positive.
Required if the value for Blind Spot Localized (0024,0106) is YES.
See

table_lines.name: Blind Spot Y-Coordinate
table_lines.comment:
The vertical coordinate of the patient's blind spot relative to the center of the patient fixation, in degrees, such that up is positive.
Required if the value for Blind Spot Localized (0024,0106) is YES.
See

table_lines.name: Minimum Sensitivity Value
table_lines.comment: The minimum sensitivity value generated by the equipment used for this visual field test, in dB.

table_lines.name: Test Point Normals Data Flag
table_lines.comment: Existence of normative data base for at least one of the test points in this set of test points.

table_lines.name: Test Point Normals Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Normative data base used for this test sequence.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Test Point Normals Data Flag (0024,0057) is YES.

table_lines.name: Age Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Algorithm Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Software algorithm used to provide the probability that the age corrected sensitivity deviation values at each test point belong to a normal visual field.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Test Point Normals Data Flag (0024,0057) is YES.

table_lines.name: Generalized Defect Sensitivity Deviation Algorithm Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Software algorithm used to provide the probability that the sensitivity deviation values at each test point belong to a normal visual field.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Test Point Normals Data Flag (0024,0057) is YES.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Test Point Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information for each test point in the visual field.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Visual Field Test Point X-Coordinate
table_lines.comment: The horizontal coordinate of a single test point relative to the center of the patient fixation, in degrees, such that toward the right is positive.

table_lines.name: >Visual Field Test Point Y-Coordinate
table_lines.comment: The vertical coordinate of a single test point relative to the center of the patient fixation, in degrees, such that up is positive.

table_lines.name: >Stimulus Results
table_lines.comment: Whether the patient saw a stimulus presented at a luminance other than maximum, a presentation at maximum luminance, or did not see any presented stimulus.

table_lines.name: >Sensitivity Value
table_lines.comment:
If Stimulus Results (0024,0093) is SEEN then this value is the sensitivity, in dB.
Required if Content Item Modifier Sequence (0040,0441) within Performed Protocol Code Sequence (0040,0260) contains an Item with the value

table_lines.name: >Retest Stimulus Seen
table_lines.comment: Whether the retested stimulus presented was seen by the patient.

table_lines.name: >Retest Sensitivity Value
table_lines.comment: If the Retest Stimulus Seen (0024,0095) is YES, then this value is the sensitivity, in dB.

table_lines.name: >Quantified Defect
table_lines.comment: Difference between the expected and the determined sensitivity, each in dB.

table_lines.name: >Visual Field Test Point Normals Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information about normal values for each visual field test point.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence. May be empty if there is no normative data for this test point.
Required if Test Point Normals Data Flag (0024,0057) is YES.

table_lines.name: >>Age Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Value
table_lines.comment: Difference between the patient's local sensitivity and the age corrected normal sensitivity, in dB.

table_lines.name: >>Age Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Probability Value
table_lines.comment: The percentile of the age corrected sensitivity deviation within the normal population of visual field, in percent.

table_lines.name: >> Generalized Defect Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether generalized defect corrected data are available for this point.

table_lines.name: >>Generalized Defect Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Value
table_lines.comment:
The age corrected sensitivity deviation after correction for the Generalized Defect, in dB. Generalized defect is proportional to the loss in sensitivity shared by all points in the visual field.
Required if Generalized Defect Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Flag (0024,0102) is YES.

table_lines.name: >>Generalized Defect Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Probability Value
table_lines.comment:
The percentile of the generalized defect corrected sensitivity deviation within the normal population of visual field, in percent.
Required if Generalized Defect Corrected Sensitivity Deviation Flag (0024,0102) is YES.

table_lines.name: Visual Field Mean Sensitivity
table_lines.comment:

table_lines.name: Visual Field Test Normals Flag

table_lines.comment:

Required if Visual Field Test Normals Flag (0024,0063) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Global Deviation from Normal

table_lines.name: >Global Deviation Probability Normals Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether normals exist for the global deviation probability.

table_lines.name: >Global Deviation Probability Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Probability value and software algorithm used to provide the normality for the global deviation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Global Deviation Probability Normals Flag (0024,0059) is YES.

table_lines.name: >>Global Deviation Probability
table_lines.comment: The percentile of the Global Deviation from Normal (0024,0066) value within the normal population, in percent.0024

table_lines.name: >Localized Deviation From Normal
table_lines.comment: Weighted square root of loss variance, in dB.

table_lines.name: >Local Deviation Probability Normals Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether normals exist for the local deviation probability.

table_lines.name: >Localized Deviation Probability Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Probability value and software algorithm used to provide the normality for the local deviation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Local Deviation Probability Normals Flag (0024,0072) is YES.

table_lines.name: >>Localized Deviation Probability
table_lines.comment: The percentile of the Localized Deviation From Normal (0024,0068) value within the normal population, in percent.

table_lines.name: Short Term Fluctuation Calculated
table_lines.comment: Whether the short term fluctuation was calculated.

table_lines.name: Short Term Fluctuation
table_lines.comment:
Average deviation of sensitivity for the repeated test locations, in dB. This is used to determine the consistency of the patient's responses.
Required if Short Term Fluctuation Calculated (0024,0074) is YES.

table_lines.name: Short Term Fluctuation Probability Calculated
