Laterality of object imaged (as described in Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218)) examined.
Shall be consistent with any laterality information contained in Primary Anatomic Structure Modifier Sequence (0008,2230), if present.

table_lines.usage:
The concept code for Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) shall be

D

C.8.30.3-1.table_caption: Corneal Topography Map Analysis Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Corneal Vertex Location
table_lines.comment:
Location of the corneal vertex. This is used for the reference point for other Attributes within this SOP Instance and determined by the Image referenced in the Attribute Source Image Sequence (0008,2112). Given as column\row. Column is the horizontal offset and row is the vertical offset.
Image relative position specified with sub-pixel resolution such that the origin at the Top Left Hand Corner (TLHC) of the TLHC pixel is 0.0\0.0, the Bottom Right Hand Corner (BRHC) of the TLHC pixel is 1.0\1.0, and the BRHC of the BRHC pixel is Columns\Rows (see
This location shall anchor the corneal vertex at the x, y and z coordinates of 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, in mm. See

table_lines.name: Corneal Topography Surface
table_lines.comment: Identifies the surface of the corneal topography map.

table_lines.name: Pupil Centroid X-Coordinate
table_lines.comment: Required if Attribute Corneal Topography Surface (0046,0201) is A (Anterior).

table_lines.name: Pupil Centroid Y-Coordinate
table_lines.comment: Required if Attribute Corneal Topography Surface (0046,0201) is A (Anterior).

table_lines.name: Equivalent Pupil Radius
table_lines.comment:
The average physical distance in mm from the pupil centroid specified in the Attributes Pupil Centroid X-Coordinate (0046,0203) and Pupil Centroid Y-Coordinate (0046,0204) to the measured perimeter of the pupil.
Required if Attribute Corneal Topography Surface (0046,0201) is A (Anterior).

table_lines.name: Vertices of the Outline of Pupil
table_lines.comment:
A set of row/column vertices that outline the perimeter of the pupil.
Two or more pairs of values follow and are the row and column coordinates of the other vertices that outline the perimeter of the pupil. For a two dimensional curve: X1, Y1, X2, Y2, etc. The first (X) dimension corresponds to the image column (horizontal offset), and the second (Y) dimension corresponds to the image row (vertical offset). This is a Polyline and the points are to be interpreted as an n-tuple list of end points between which straight lines are to be drawn.
Required if Attribute Corneal Topography Surface (0046,0201) is A (Anterior).

table_lines.name: Minimum Keratometric Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the lowest power obtained when averaging individual meridian.
Only one Item shall be permitted.

table_lines.name: >Radius of Curvature
table_lines.comment: The radius of curvature of the principal meridian of the cornea, measured in mm.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridian, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian where the keratometric radius of curvature or power is measured, measured in degrees.

table_lines.name: Simulated Keratometric Cylinder Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies simulated keratometric cylinder power of the corneal surface, measured in diopters.
Only one Item shall be permitted.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Power
table_lines.comment: The refractive power of the cornea at the principal meridian, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: >Keratometric Axis
table_lines.comment: The meridian where the keratometric cylinder or power is measured, measured in degrees.

table_lines.name: Average Corneal Power
table_lines.comment: The area-corrected average of the corneal power ahead of the entrance pupil, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: Corneal I-S Value
table_lines.comment: Quantifies the inferior-superior dioptric asymmetry along the vertical meridian to discriminate Keratoconus, measured in diopters.

table_lines.name: Analyzed Area
table_lines.comment: The corneal surface area that can be analyzed, measured in mm squared.

table_lines.name: Maximum Corneal Curvature Sequence
table_lines.comment: A Sequence to convey the maximum curvature and location of the measured corneal topography. Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Maximum Corneal Curvature
table_lines.comment: Maximum curvature in diopters of the measured corneal topography.

table_lines.name: >Maximum Corneal Curvature Location
table_lines.comment:
Location of the corneal maximum curvature.
Given as column\row. Column is the horizontal offset and row is the vertical offset.
Image relative position specified with sub-pixel resolution such that the origin at the Top Left Hand Corner (TLHC) of the TLHC pixel is 0.0\0.0, the Bottom Right Hand Corner (BRHC) of the TLHC pixel is 1.0\1.0, and the BRHC of the BRHC pixel is Columns\Rows (see

table_lines.name: Surface Regularity Index
table_lines.comment: Measures local fluctuations in corneal power (i.e., irregular astigmatism) over the pupil (no units).

table_lines.name: Surface Asymmetry Index
table_lines.comment: This index sums the meridional mire-to-mire power changes over the entire corneal surface, increasing as topographic irregularities increase (no units).

table_lines.name: Corneal Eccentricity Index
table_lines.comment: Index used to measure the eccentricity of the cornea (no units).

table_lines.name: Keratoconus Prediction Index
table_lines.comment: Index used to indicate the presence of Keratoconus (no units)

table_lines.name: Decimal Potential Visual Acuity
table_lines.comment: The range of best spectacle-corrected distance that might be expected from a functionally normal eye with the topographical characteristics of the analyzed cornea, measured in decimal.

table_lines.name: Corneal Topography Map Quality Evaluation
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the quality of the topography examination.
Required if a quality rating value exists for the corneal topography map

table_lines.name: Corneal Topography Map Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The type of corneal topography map encoded in this SOP Instance. It specifies the meaning of the pixel values.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Corneal Topography Mapping Normals Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the Externally Sourced Data Set used for corneal topography mapping values from a normative data base. Required if a normative data base was used.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Source Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The Image SOP Class/Instance pair of the Image that was used to generate this corneal topography map.
See
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Describes the purpose for which the reference is made, (i.e., the role the source image or frame(s) played in the generation of this image). Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Source Image Corneal Processed Data Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be present.

table_lines.name: >Corneal Point Location
table_lines.comment: The x, y, and z coordinate of a point in the image within the cornea, in mm. Where the origin is conveyed by the Attribute Corneal Vertex Location (0046,0202).

table_lines.name: >Corneal Point Estimated
table_lines.comment: The point defined in Attribute Corneal Point Location (0046,0247) is an estimated point (i.e., interpolated or extrapolated; not an actual measured point).

table_lines.name: >Axial Power
table_lines.comment:
r
Conveys corneal shape characteristics, in diopters. It is determined from the curvature,

table_lines.name: >Tangential Power
table_lines.comment: Determined from the curvature (2nd derivative = d2y/dx2) of a point on the cornea, in diopters; also called Instantaneous Power. Emphasizes irregular astigmatism (large variations in higher order aberrations).

table_lines.name: >Refractive Power
table_lines.comment: Conveys the optical refraction properties of the cornea, in diopters. It is determined from ray tracing using Snell's Law to calculate the true refractive power.

table_lines.name: >Relative Elevation
table_lines.comment: Relative elevation, in micrometers, is calculated from the corneal surface distance from a reference surface (i.e., a sphere or ellipsoid) that intersects the corneal vertex. This value is determined from z - z

table_lines.name: >Corneal Wavefront
table_lines.comment: Corneal wavefront, in micrometers, is calculated from the elevation data by fitting with the Zernike Series expansion.

table_lines.name: Positioner Motion
table_lines.comment:
Describes the activity of the X-Ray Source during acquisition.
See

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time that the acquisition of data that resulted in this image started.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment:
The time in seconds needed for the compete acquisition.
See

table_lines.name: KVP
table_lines.comment: Average of the peak kilo voltage outputs of the X-Ray generator used for all frames.

table_lines.name: X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment:
Average of the nominal X-Ray tube currents in milliamperes for all frames.
Required if Exposure in mAs (0018,9332) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Exposure Time in ms
table_lines.comment:
Total (cumulative) duration of X-Ray exposure for all acquired frames in milliseconds.
Required if Exposure in mAs (0018,9332) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment:
The total (cumulative) exposure for all acquired frames expressed in mAs, for example calculated from Exposure Time and X-Ray Tube Current.
Required if either Exposure Time in ms (0018,9328) or X-Ray Tube Current in mA (0018,9330) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Focal Spot(s)
table_lines.comment: Nominal focal spot size in mm used to acquire all frames.

table_lines.name: Anode Target Material
table_lines.comment: The primary material in the anode of the X-Ray source.

table_lines.name: Body Part Thickness
table_lines.comment: The average thickness in mm of the body part examined when compressed, if compression has been applied during exposure.

table_lines.name: Compression Force
table_lines.comment: The compression force applied to the body part during exposure, measured in Newtons.

table_lines.name: Compression Pressure
table_lines.comment: The average compression pressure applied to the body part during exposure, calculated in kPa.

table_lines.name: Compression Contact Area
table_lines.comment: The area of the body part to which compression has been applied during exposure, measured in mm2.

table_lines.name: Paddle Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the compression paddle, if compression was applied to the body part during exposure.

table_lines.name: Exposure Control Mode
table_lines.comment: Type of exposure control

table_lines.name: Exposure Control Mode Description
table_lines.comment:
Text description of the mechanism of exposure control.
May describe the number and type of exposure sensors or position of the sensitive area of the imaging detector.

table_lines.name: Patient Orientation
table_lines.comment:
Patient direction of the rows and columns of the most representative frame.
Required if View Code Sequence (0054,0220) has an Item value other than one representing a specimen image. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Image Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments about the image.

table_lines.name: Samples per Pixel
table_lines.comment: Number of samples (planes) in this image.

table_lines.name: Photometric Interpretation
table_lines.comment: Specifies the intended interpretation of the pixel data.

table_lines.name: Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits allocated.

table_lines.name: Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample. Each sample shall have the same number of bits stored.

table_lines.name: High Bit
table_lines.comment:
Most significant bit for pixel sample data. Each sample shall have the same high bit.
Shall have an Enumerated Value of one less than the value of Bits Stored (0028,0101).

table_lines.name: Pixel Representation
table_lines.comment: Data representation of the pixel samples. Each sample shall have the same pixel representation.

table_lines.name: Quality Control Image
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not this image is a quality control of phantom image.

table_lines.name: Burned in Annotation
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not the image contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the image was acquired.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether an Image has undergone lossy compression (at a point in its lifetime).
Once this value has been set to 01 it shall not be reset.
See

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Method
table_lines.comment:
A label for the lossy compression method(s) that have been applied to this image.
See
Required if Lossy Image Compression (0028,2110) is "01".

table_lines.name: Organ Dose
table_lines.comment: Organ dose value measured in dGy representing the collective total for all acquired frames.

table_lines.name: Entrance Dose in mGy
table_lines.comment: Entrance dose value measured in mGy at the surface of the patient representing the collective total for all acquired frames.

table_lines.name: Entrance Dose Derivation
table_lines.comment: Describes what type of dose is represented by the values of Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302).

table_lines.name: Type of Detector Motion
table_lines.comment:
Describes the activity of the Detector during acquisition.
See

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment: This icon image is representative of the Image. Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment: Specifies a transformation for the Presentation LUT such that the output of all grayscale transformations, if any, is defined to be in P-Values.

table_lines.name: Positioner Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the geometrical position of the positioner.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Signed position in degrees of the X-Ray beam vector in the coronal anatomical plane as if the patient were standing facing the equipment where vertical is zero.
Required if X-Ray source can be moved in the coronal anatomical plane. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Primary Angle Direction
table_lines.comment:
The interpretation of the sign of the Positioner Primary Angle (0018,1510).
See
Required if Positioner Primary Angle (0018,1510) is present.

table_lines.name: >Positioner Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Position in degrees of the X-Ray beam vector in the sagittal anatomical plane as if the patient were standing where movement of the X-Ray source from anterior to posterior is positive, and vertical is zero.
Required if the X-Ray source can be moved in the sagittal anatomical plane. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Detector Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the geometrical position of the detector.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Detector Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in the row direction in degrees relative to the normal to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward higher numbered columns. Negative values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward lower numbered columns.
See
Required if the detector can be moved in the row direction. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Angle of the X-Ray beam in the column direction in degrees relative to the normal to the detector plane. Positive values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward lower numbered rows. Negative values indicate that the X-Ray beam is tilted toward higher numbered rows.
See
Required if the detector can be moved in the column direction. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: X-Ray Geometry Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the geometric properties for this frame or set of frames.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment:
Distance in mm from source to detector center on the chest wall line.
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008,0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Patient
table_lines.comment:
Distance in mm from source to the Breast Support side that is closest to the Imaging Subject, as measured along the X-Ray beam vector.
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008,0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Distance from source to isocenter in mm.
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008,0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Distance Source to Entrance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm from the source to the surface of the patient closest to the source during the acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: >Estimated Radiographic Magnification Factor
table_lines.comment: Ratio of Source Image Distance (SID) over Source Object Distance (SOD).

C.8.31.5-1.table_caption: Breast X-Ray Acquisition Dose Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: X-Ray Acquisition Dose Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the X-Ray exposure information for this frame.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Exposure Time in ms
table_lines.comment: Duration of X-Ray exposure in milliseconds.

table_lines.name: >Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment: The exposure expressed in mAs, for example calculated from Exposure Time and X-Ray Tube Current.

table_lines.name: >Relative X-Ray Exposure
table_lines.comment: Indication of the applied dose, in manufacturer specific units.

table_lines.name: >Half Value Layer
table_lines.comment: The thickness of Aluminum in mm required to reduce the X-Ray Output (0040,0312) by a factor of two.

table_lines.name: >Organ Dose
table_lines.comment: Average organ dose value measured in dGy during the acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: >Entrance Dose in mGy
table_lines.comment: Average entrance dose value measured in mGy at the surface of the patient during the acquisition of this image.

table_lines.name: >Entrance Dose Derivation
table_lines.comment: Describes what type of dose is represented by the values of Entrance Dose in mGy (0040,8302).

C.8.31.6-1.table_caption: Breast X-Ray Isocenter Reference System Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Isocenter Reference System Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that describes the Isocenter Reference Coordinate System (O, X, Y, Z).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Source Isocenter Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Primary angle of the X-Ray source in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >X-Ray Source Isocenter Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Secondary angle of the X-Ray source in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Breast Support Isocenter Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Primary angle of the Breast Support in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Breast Support Isocenter Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Secondary angle of the Breast Support in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Breast Support X Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
X position of the Breast Support Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Breast Support Y Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Y position of the Breast Support Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Breast Support Z Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Z position of the Breast Support Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Isocenter Primary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Primary angle of the Detector in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Detector Isocenter Secondary Angle
table_lines.comment:
Secondary angle of the Detector in the in the isocenter reference system (deg).
See

table_lines.name: >Detector X Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
X position of the Detector Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Y Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Y position of the Detector Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Z Position to Isocenter
table_lines.comment:
Z position of the Detector Reference Point with respect to the Isocenter (mm).
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Active Area TLHC Position
table_lines.comment:
The x, y, and z coordinates in mm of the center of the top left hand corner detector element of the detector active area in the Detector coordinate system.
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Detector Active Area Orientation
table_lines.comment:
The direction cosines of the first row and the first column with respect to the Detector coordinate system.
See
Required if Presentation Intent Type (0008.0068) = FOR PROCESSING. May be present otherwise.
